ny = research; copy from one = plagiarism -- *Speaker: GARRETT Robbins*\n\n### L2 - MENTAL MODELS\n\n- **MM-RB-7FS-003** -- Towards-pleasure vs. Away-from-pain segmentation: 90% pain / 10% pleasure (specific ratio) -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-004** -- State change model for selling: online = protected/low-trust, in-person = social proof state; high-ticket needs state change event -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-005** -- Dollar-per-lead (DPL) mental model: evaluate every traffic source by DPL, not conversion rate alone ($50 DPL example) -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-006** -- A/B/C Lead Segmentation Model: A leads called immediately, B leads get sequence, C leads go to nurture -- *Speaker: GARRETT Robbins*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-008** -- \"Magic Money Machine\" concept: $1 in = $1+ out consistently, then maximize traffic -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-011** -- Audience-first traffic model: research competitors via Adbeat/Quantcast before spending -- *Speaker: EXT-SCOTT*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-012** -- Digital convergence marketing model: radio creates mass traffic, digital tail converts -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-013** -- List hierarchy: Buyers > Responders > Compiled; compiled lists are worthless for DR -- *Speaker: EXT-LUKE*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-014** -- Elephant offer mental model: absurdly high-priced offer makes all other offers seem reasonable -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-015** -- Lead aging model: leads aged up to 40 days can triple volume -- *Speaker: GARRETT Robbins*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-016** -- Info product as affiliate army creation: educational product automatically trains affiliates -- *Speaker: RB*\n\n### L3 - HEURISTICS\n\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-001** -- First backend offer: $1,000 coaching x 79 people = $79,000 from one email -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-002** -- Sales commission for closers: 15-20% of closed deal value -- *Speaker: GARRETT/RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-003** -- Subscription continuation retention: 15-20% passive vs. 75-80% active (Scott Holman model) -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-004** -- 3x price increase ($30 to $97/month) can double profitability -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-005** -- Live event streaming: charge $300 vs. $5,000 in-person, $30K-$60K additional revenue -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-006** -- Order form two-step test: credit card warning decreases step-1 (70%->60%) but step-2 jumps 3%->27% -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-007** -- Optimized headline lifts conversion from 1% to 2.5-3% = 2.5-3x buyers -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-008** -- Email follow-up multiplier: 14 sales -> 130 sales with autoresponder = 9.3x -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-009** -- Exit pop adds $60K/month additional revenue from existing traffic -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-010** -- Backend ascension pricing ladder: $10->$20->$40->$50->$350->$2K->$10K -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-011** -- $2 CPL -> $50 DPL = 25x ROAS when backend is properly monetized -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-012** -- PatLive inbound call conversion with trained scripts -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-013** -- First workshop: 5 attendees x $5,500 = $27,500 -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-014** -- Facebook: 55 min/day, 70% daily login (dated ~2012 data) -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-015** -- YouTube: 32 hours uploaded/min, 6 videos/day per user (dated) -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-016** -- Squeeze page 12-20% conversion vs. blog <5% -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-017** -- Co-registration leads: $0.05-$0.10 per name via Core Edge -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-018** -- 90/10 budget split at scale: 90% proven winners, 10% testing -- *Speaker: EXT-SCOTT*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-019** -- Payday loan CPA: 100-200 calls/day, $30 cost/$100 CPA/$70 net = 70% margin -- *Speaker: EXT-MICHAEL*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-020** -- Direct mail test: always 2,000 pieces minimum before scaling to 5,000 -- *Speaker: EXT-LUKE*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-021** -- Hotline list: 10,000+ new names/month, universe 2+ years old -- *Speaker: EXT-LUKE*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-022** -- Radio CPM: industry $4.54 vs. Bulldozer Digital $2 -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-023** -- Radio response benchmark: 60 calls per $1,000 spend = success -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-024** -- Radio ROI target: 2.3:1 return on ad spend -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-025** -- Priceline case study: 2.2M responses in 14 days, $1B in 18 months -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-026** -- Shatner deal: 90,000 shares + small cash -> eventually $600M -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-027** -- Ford Explorer social media: 200% better ROI than Super Bowl ad -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-028** -- Upsell conversion: up to 50% on hot buyers -- *Speaker: EXT-PATRICK*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-029** -- Squeeze page + sales page produces MORE sales than direct-to-sales-page; 50% opt-in -- *Speaker: EXT-PATRICK*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-030** -- Non-buyer re-exposure: 3-5 exposures needed before buying -- *Speaker: EXT-PATRICK*\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-031** -- 18-year-old case study: $10K/month ads -> webinar -> $500K in 3 months -- *Speaker: RB*\n\n### L4 - FRAMEWORKS\n\n- **FW-RB-7FS-002** -- Backend Program Structure: 4 elements (high-ticket, info-based, live component, application barrier) -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-003** -- Strategy Session Sales Framework: naming it \"strategy session\" vs. \"sales call\" increases show rate -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-004** -- \"Let Them Sell Themselves\" Framework: questions structure so prospect articulates own gap -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-005** -- Sales psychology sequence: emotion -> logic -> fear of loss (in that order) -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-006** -- Landing Page Segmentation: separate pages for each pain cluster, segment by mindset -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-009** -- Affiliate Recruiting Framework: 3 types (list owners, Google rankers, ad runners) -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-010** -- Media Buying Testing Framework: 4 steps (choose, test, record, optimize+scale) -- *Speaker: EXT-SCOTT*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-011** -- Social Media Attractive Character: 5 elements (quirks, real stories, pets/lifestyle, adventures, strong opinions) -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-012** -- Personal Brand as Serial Fiction Model: dynamic, layered, intentional, serial (Harry Potter analogy) -- *Speaker: EXT-RACHEL*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-013** -- SEO Attack Framework: 4 phases (site analysis, competitor analysis, keyword optimization, link building) -- *Speaker: EXT-MICHAEL*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-014** -- Email List Rental: 5 criteria (niche match, proven buyers, recency, multi-use, specialized broker) -- *Speaker: EXT-PATRICK*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-015** -- Postcard Direct Mail: 6 elements of \"official style\" postcard (Courier, no return address, etc.) -- *Speaker: EXT-LUKE*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-016** -- Radio Ad 15-Part Formula: Fred Katona's complete radio commercial formula -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-017** -- Double Trust Agent with Backstory Framework (radio + social integration) -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-019** -- New Lead Funnel Architecture: name+email+phone -> webinar -> Philippines call floor -> coaching offer -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **FW-RB-7FS-020** -- Voice Broadcasting Backend Follow-Up: recorded message to cold leads driving to webinar/callback -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n\n### L5 - METHODOLOGIES\n\n- **MET-RB-7FS-001** -- First Backend Launch: build list, $1K coaching offer, one email, phone calls, record, productize -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-002** -- Workshop Launch: 5 people x $5,500, 2-day intensive, record, sell recordings -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-003** -- Subscription Continuation Setup (Scott Holman Model): default continue at $500/month, 75-80% retention -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-004** -- Backend Application Process: application -> A/B lead filter -> strategy session -> emotional alignment -> close with urgency -- *Speaker: GARRETT*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-006** -- Post-Event Action Planning (Tony Robbins-derived): letter to self, extract 3 actions, commit to 1 on plane -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-008** -- Lead Gen for MLM/Network Marketing: landing page for opportunity, autoresponder, leverage personality brand -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-009** -- Facebook Ads for CPA: find $100+ CPA offer, emotional one-sentence ad, disruptive image, broad targeting -- *Speaker: EXT-MICHAEL*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-010** -- Affiliate Program Launch: EPC-focused offer, swipe files, recruit from Google/Facebook advertisers, co-registration at $0.05-$0.10 -- *Speaker: RB*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-011** -- Direct Mail Postcard Campaign: Nextmark list search, verify hotline/universe, test 2K pieces, scale to 5K+ -- *Speaker: EXT-LUKE*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-012** -- Radio Commercial Creation (Fred Katona 15-Part Formula): complete step-by-step, $1,500-$3,000 local test budget -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-013** -- Radio Campaign Launch: local test -> measure 60+ responses/$1K -> national test -> scale + digital tail overlay -- *Speaker: EXT-FRED*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-014** -- Media Buying Scaling: single source, test 3-5 ads, 90/10 budget split after 1K clicks, then scale -- *Speaker: EXT-SCOTT*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-015** -- Email List Rental Campaign: list broker, buyers lists, multi-use rate, squeeze page, 50% upsell conversion, resell 3-5x -- *Speaker: EXT-PATRICK*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-016** -- Competitor Ads Research via Adbeat: enter domain, find longest-running ads, click through to landing pages, map funnel -- *Speaker: EXT-SCOTT*\n- **MET-RB-7FS-017** -- Live Event Streaming Monetization: $300 streaming x 100-200 seats = $30K-$60K -- *Speaker: RB*\n\n---\n\n## ENRICHMENTS (to update existing)\n\n- **PHI-RB-005** (front-end = break even) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-001 adds specific \"backend is where ALL the money is made\" framing and the lead-generation-engine language from 7FS context\n- **PHI-RB-021** (people silently begging to be led) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-003 adds Jay Abraham attribution explicitly\n- **PHI-RB-009** (implementation over consumption) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-009 adds the \"act first, perfect later\" variation (\"stop waiting until it's perfect\")\n- **PHI-RB-072** (pay affiliates more) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-015 adds specific leverage math: one affiliate with 100K list = 10x more reach than solo ads, pay only after sale\n- **MM-RB-002** (Value Ladder) <-- MM-RB-7FS-001 adds the \"each rung up is a higher price point\" simple metaphor and \"lifeline of a lead\" lifecycle stages\n- **MM-RB-003** (Big Domino) <-- Not directly enriched but MM-RB-7FS-002 \"Lifeline of a Lead\" is a related but distinct model (stranger -> subscriber -> buyer -> hyperactive buyer -> continuity)\n- **L2 Away-from-Pain** (line 847 in DNA.yaml) <-- MM-RB-7FS-003 adds specific 90/10 ratio (mass market 90% pain, 10% pleasure)\n- **MM-RB Pre-Frame Bridge** (MM at line 558) <-- MM-RB-7FS-009 reinforces the concept with specific quote\n- **HEUR-RB (7 touches)** (line 1180) <-- FW-RB-7FS-008 adds \"10 years ago it was fewer, now with all the noise it might be more\" context\n- **HEUR-RB (50% emotion, 30% logic, 20% fear)** (line 1568) <-- FW-RB-7FS-005 from GARRETT adds the practical sequence: emotion first, logic to justify, fear to close\n- **FW Funnel Hacking** (line 612, 2189) <-- FW-RB-7FS-007 adds \"bought P90X three times\" anecdote and \"steal what works ethically\" framing\n- **MET Funnel Hacking Process** (line 2189) <-- MET-RB-7FS-007 adds explicit 6-step competitor funnel research methodology (buy, go through, map in spreadsheet, identify gaps, model)\n- **MET-RB Email Follow-Up** (existing autoresponder concepts) <-- MET-RB-7FS-005 adds segmentation by action (clicked/bought/didn't open), 3-5 resells to non-buyers, hyperactive buyers get backend immediately\n\n---\n\n## DUPLICATES (skip)\n\n- **PHI-RB-7FS-002** (content quality > production quality) -- Covered by PHI-RB-009 (implementation over consumption) and general RB philosophy\n- **PHI-RB-7FS-005** (investment creates accountability) -- Covered by PHI-RB-029 enrichment (Expert Secrets p.248 \"getting people to give you money is accountability\")\n- **PHI-RB-7FS-006** (personality-based marketing as moat) -- Covered by PHI-RB-012 (price resistance disappears with movement), Attractive Character Model (MM-RB at line 507)\n- **PHI-RB-7FS-007** (buyers list is most valuable asset) -- Covered by PHI-RB-040 (buyer is a buyer is a buyer) and hyperactive buyer model\n- **PHI-RB-7FS-008** (polarization) -- Covered by Attractive Character Model (MM-RB line 507) and Howard Stern example already in DNA\n- **MM-RB-7FS-001** (Value Ladder) -- Duplicate of MM-RB-002\n- **MM-RB-7FS-007** (Three levers to grow: more customers, higher transaction, more frequency) -- Jay Abraham principle, generally known but not explicitly in DNA. *Reclassified to NEW.*\n- **MM-RB-7FS-010** (Attractive Character 6 elements) -- Duplicate of MM-RB at line 507 and FW Attractive Character at line 1680\n- **FW-RB-7FS-001** (Attractive Character Framework) -- Duplicate of FW at line 1680\n- **FW-RB-7FS-018** (Buyer Segmentation 3-tier) -- Duplicate of existing buyer segmentation in MM and HEUR layers\n\n**Total duplicates: 9**\n\n---\n\n## RECLASSIFICATION NOTE\n\nMM-RB-7FS-007 (Three levers to grow a business -- Jay Abraham) was initially flagged as potential duplicate but does NOT exist explicitly in the DNA.yaml. Reclassified to NEW.\n\n---\n\n## STATS\n\n| Metric | Count |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Total extracted** | 102 |\n| **New** | 80 |\n| **Enrichments** | 13 |\n| **Duplicates** | 9 |\n\n### New elements by layer:\n\n| Layer | New | Enrichments |\n|-------|-----|-------------|\n| L1 Philosophies | 9 | 4 |\n| L2 Mental Models | 12 (incl. reclassified MM-7) | 4 |\n| L3 Heuristics | 31 | 0 |\n| L4 Frameworks | 16 | 2 |\n| L5 Methodologies | 15 | 3 |\n\n### New elements by speaker:\n\n| Speaker | New Elements |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Russell Brunson (RB) | ~33 |\n| GARRETT Robbins | ~10 |\n| EXT-FRED (Fred Katona, Radio) | ~12 |\n| EXT-SCOTT (Media Buying) | ~5 |\n| EXT-RACHEL (Social) | ~7 |\n| EXT-LUKE (Direct Mail) | ~6 |\n| EXT-PATRICK (Email Media Buying) | ~5 |\n| EXT-MICHAEL (SEO/CPA) | ~3 |\n\n### Key Observations:\n\n1. **Guest speaker content is almost entirely NEW** -- the existing 470-element DNA is sourced from Secrets Masterclass + PDF books + High Ticket Secrets + Perfect Webinar Secrets. The 7 Figure Shortcut guest speakers (Fred Katona on radio, Scott on media buying, Luke on direct mail, Rachel on social, Patrick on email media buying, Michael on SEO) are completely absent from existing DNA.\n\n2. **Russell Brunson's own content from 7FS has high overlap on PRINCIPLES** (philosophies and mental models) but is largely NEW on SPECIFICS -- the concrete numbers, case studies, and backend-specific heuristics are not in the existing DNA even when the general concept is.\n\n3. **GARRETT Robbins content is entirely new** -- he was not a speaker in any previously processed source.\n\n4. **The L3 Heuristics layer is the richest** -- 31 new elements, most with specific numbers and thresholds that do not exist in the current DNA even when the concept is familiar. These are high-value additions.\n\n5. **Some dated data** -- HEUR-RB-7FS-014 and -015 (Facebook/YouTube stats from ~2012) should be tagged with a `[DATED ~2012]` flag when added to DNA to prevent citing them as current.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>138324</total_tokens><tool_uses>26</tool_uses><duration_ms>209009</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a7e8820c56f2f73be.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-04T11:32:38.733394", "_id": "94443495"}
