**NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-087** -- EPC as Universal Traffic Currency. Formul", "metadata": {"session_id": "7eac16a0-69d1-409c-a5c6-7ab6cb49d53e", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\7eac16a0-69d1-409c-a5c6-7ab6cb49d53e.jsonl", "cwd": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\Downloads\\mega-brain-premium", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>ad85028e5acbb258b</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01PRTrddsYFuAjoGfAc9j72s</tool-use-id>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Batch A: dedup merge analysis\" completed</summary>\n<result>I now have comprehensive data for the full analysis. Here is the report:\n\n---\n\n# BATCH A DEDUP ANALYSIS\n## Source: 07-7-FIGURE-SHORTCUT-DNA.md (70 elements) vs DNA.yaml (429 elements)\n\n---\n\n## NEW ELEMENTS (to add)\n\n### L1 PHILOSOPHIES (5 new)\n\n- **[L1] PHI-RB-087** -- \"Pain-motivated buyers are 90% of the world; 90% of entrepreneurs market toward pleasure\" -- the 90/90 mismatch. Existing DNA has the \"Away from Pain vs Toward Pleasure\" model (MM-RB line 847) but NOT this specific 90/90 stat and mismatch philosophy. **NEW with numbers.**\n- **[L1] PHI-RB-088** -- \"Content alone is not enough -- context (relationship) is what sells.\" Gary Vaynerchuk insight RB adopted. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L1] PHI-RB-089** -- \"Lead or Gold\" -- set hard deadlines as if life depends on it. Gary Halbert concept (Code of Arms letter). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L1] PHI-RB-090** -- Offline and internet traffic are complementary -- internet plateaus, offline scales infinitely. Vince James $100M in 23 months reference. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L1] PHI-RB-091** -- Test small, reinvest, scale -- never bet the farm on unproven traffic. Compounding philosophy from Vince James example. Not in existing DNA at this level of specificity. **NEW.**\n\n### L2 MENTAL MODELS (7 new)\n\n- **[L2] MM-RB-085** -- The Webinar Attendance Funnel (4-Segment Model): Registered-No-Show, Showed, Saw-Offer, Buyers. Distinct behavioral segments for follow-up. Existing DNA has retargeting segments and webinar funnel but NOT this specific 4-segment registrant model. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-086** -- The Modality Switching Framework: audio, video, text, physical across follow-up touches. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-087** -- EPC as Universal Traffic Currency. Formula: Total Revenue / Total Clicks = EPC. Makes all traffic sources comparable. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-088** -- The Traffic Rollout Stack: Own list -> JV -> Solo ads -> SEO -> Ad networks. Ordered by cost/risk, each funded by previous stage. Not in existing DNA at this level. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-089** -- Traffic Personality Matching: different traffic types suit different operator personalities. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-090** -- Pattern Matching for Ad Copy: solo ad copy must match voice/tone of newsletter. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L2] MM-RB-091** -- The Internet-as-Real-Estate Model: top-ranked sites are prime real estate lots; buy \"lots\" rather than compete for rankings. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n\n### L3 HEURISTICS (24 new)\n\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-158** -- First 10 min of webinar = 50% of total drop-off. Hook must be in these minutes. Not in existing DNA with this specificity. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-159** -- $1,000 is optimal high-ticket webinar price point (no spousal approval needed). Russell sold 79 units at $1K = $79K. Existing has $997 mentioned in funnel context but NOT this specific \"no-approval threshold\" reasoning. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-160** -- Hand-sketch pattern interrupt on squeeze page = 57% opt-in rate. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-161** -- 30% of webinar registrants provide cell phone if asked. Text before/after webinar. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-162** -- 10-20% of webinar buyers take immediate upsell. Not in existing DNA with this percentage. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-163** -- Downsell mini-kit at 50% discount to webinar non-buyers. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-164** -- Good affiliate EPC = $2-5. At $5+ affiliates come to you. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-165** -- Solo ads in IM space cost ~$0.30/click. Conservative newsletter readers convert well for IM (90% skew conservative). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-166** -- Never reveal actual dollar profits to solo ad sellers. Rate 1-10 instead. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-167** -- Mail to 2-3 solo ad lists per week to spread risk. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-168** -- Always negotiate make-good clause in solo ad/media buy insertion orders. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-169** -- Contact Dream 100 every 2 weeks via lumpy mail + phone. Not in existing DNA with this frequency. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-170** -- Montblanc pen ($140 from Costco) via FedEx when affiliate agrees to promote. Psychological reciprocity. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-171** -- Top keyword \"make money\" = 50K organic visitors/month. #1 site = 300K-400K/month. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-172** -- Blog minimum 3x/week for SEO. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-173** -- $300/month banner on well-ranked site = 100+ opt-ins/day. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-174** -- Thrifty Nickel nationwide classified = ~$280-300. Cheapest offline test vehicle. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-175** -- Craigslist ~$3/posted ad, ~3 clicks per ad. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-176** -- Tear sheets (fake newspaper articles) = 30-45x response rate vs postcards, near 100% open rate. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-177** -- Registration page video 60-75 sec with intro music = 10-12% lift. Not in existing DNA (existing DNA says \"videos ALWAYS destroy conversion\" on reg pages -- this is a CONTRADICTION, note below). **NEW (with conflict note).**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-178** -- Max $1,000 per new traffic source test. Turn off if not profitable at $1K-$2K. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-179** -- In offline classified ads, always use phone number (not URL). Phone always outperforms URL in print. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-180** -- Woman's name for phone CTA increases offline ad conversions. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L3] HEUR-RB-181** -- Second-tier affiliate commission at 10% creates self-expanding affiliate army. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n\n### L4 FRAMEWORKS (8 new)\n\n- **[L4] FW-RB-097** -- The 4-List Behavioral Segmentation System (Registered-No-Show / Showed / Saw-Offer / Buyers with tech stack: A-Weber + SendGrid/Amazon SES). Not in existing DNA at this operational level. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-098** -- The Media Buying Ladder (MSN AdCenter -> Text Ads -> PPV -> Display -> Retargeting -> AI-Optimized). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-099** -- The Offline Direct Mail Escalation System (3 phases: Classifieds -> Postcards -> Tear Sheets, each funded by previous). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-100** -- The Affiliate Creation System: creating new affiliates from existing customers (Marlin Sanders model, David Fry model, Nanocast, co-op buys). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-101** -- The Webinar Swap / Ad Swap System: reciprocal promotion framework for list-owners. Not in existing DNA at this operational level. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-102** -- The Integration Marketing Touchpoints System (6 points: thank-you pages, purchase pages, day-14 email swap, email footer, PS swap, physical mailings). Existing DNA mentions integration marketing concept broadly but NOT these 6 specific touchpoints. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-103** -- The Solo Ad Testing and Scaling System (find lists, test with Archimax banner first, pattern-match copy, pre-frame page, HyperTracker, rate 1-10, make-good clauses). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L4] FW-RB-104** -- The SEO Authority Site Blueprint (opt-in sandwich, keyword research, blog content, onsite optimization, offsite link building, social signals, search engine banner ads). Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n\n### L5 METHODOLOGIES (4 new)\n\n- **[L5] MET-RB-048** -- Launching Your First Automated Webinar (90-Day Sprint): 11-step operational sequence from offer definition to hiring concierge team. Not in existing DNA as a unified methodology. **NEW.**\n- **[L5] MET-RB-049** -- Building a $10K/Day Affiliate Network from Scratch: 13-step complete process from Dream 100 to creating customers-as-affiliates. Not in existing DNA as a unified methodology. **NEW.**\n- **[L5] MET-RB-050** -- Testing a New Traffic Source ($1,000 Protocol): standardized testing methodology with budget caps, decision gates, and scaling rules. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n- **[L5] MET-RB-051** -- SEO Authority Site Build (6-Month Organic Traffic Machine): month-by-month execution plan with specific tools and benchmarks. Not in existing DNA. **NEW.**\n\n---\n\n## ENRICHMENTS (to update existing)\n\n### L1 PHILOSOPHIES (3 enrichments)\n\n- **PHI-RB-004/005** (outspend competition / front-end break even) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-001 adds the specific origin story: $30/month membership -> $30K week selling $500 coaching to same 300-400 members. Reinforces with new numerical example. **ENRICH with 7FS context.**\n- **PHI-RB-059** (Dig Your Well Before You're Thirsty / relationships) <-- PHI-RB-7FS-008 and PHI-RB-7FS-009 add operational detail: \"Rule #1: Don't be a jerk\", become JV broker first, serve before asking. **ENRICH with execution principles.**\n- **PHI-RB-059** <-- PHI-RB-7FS-010 adds Jay Abraham's \"customer lifeline\" framework (pre-product and post-product partners). **ENRICH with specific partner identification method.**\n\n### L2 MENTAL MODELS (2 enrichments)\n\n- **MM-RB Pre-Frame Bridge (line 558)** <-- MM-RB-7FS-006 adds the specific metaphor: \"toll booth between the highway and the theme park\" and cold traffic requirement for intermediate page. **ENRICH with metaphor and application detail.**\n- **MM-RB-052 / Retargeting Framework (line 2083)** <-- MM-RB-7FS-011 adds the specific math: of 100 clicks, only 30-40% register, remaining 60-70% are warm prospects worth retargeting at banner rates. **ENRICH with conversion funnel numbers.**\n\n### L3 HEURISTICS (2 enrichments)\n\n- **HEUR-RB (trial close, line 2274)** <-- HEUR-RB-7FS-003 provides the \"75% conversion increase\" figure for trial closes. Existing DNA has \"74% improvement\" ($9.45 to $16.50). This is essentially the same stat from a different source -- note as **cross-source reinforcement.**\n- **HEUR-RB (webinar close rate, line 1090)** <-- HEUR-RB-7FS-002 restates the $1K price point benchmark and close rate data. **ENRICH with the 79-unit / $79K / 7-day specific case study.**\n\n### L4 FRAMEWORKS (3 enrichments)\n\n- **FW-RB (The Stack, line 352 area)** <-- FW-RB-7FS-002 adds Armand Morin attribution and the specific 5-7 element stacking structure with running total reveal. Existing DNA captures the Stack but 7FS adds structural detail. **ENRICH with step-by-step mechanics.**\n- **FW-RB Dream 100 (line 1934)** <-- FW-RB-7FS-007 adds granular operational detail: research their families, pizza deliveries, dollar store items, phone follow-up cadence. Existing DNA has Dream 100 at strategic level; this adds tactical execution layer. **ENRICH with tactical execution.**\n- **FW-RB webinar indoctrination (line 2360)** <-- FW-RB-7FS-005 (The Intensification Process) adds the 3-video framework with specific structure: Big Problem, Why Solutions Failed, New Mechanism. Existing DNA mentions \"3 pre-sell videos\" but this adds the framework naming and structure. **ENRICH with named framework.**\n\n### L5 METHODOLOGIES (2 enrichments)\n\n- **MET-RB (webinar build process, exists at various points)** <-- MET-RB-7FS-005 (JV Campaign 30-Day Sequence) adds a detailed week-by-week execution plan for JV-powered launches with specific touchpoints. Existing DNA has JV strategy but not as a sequenced methodology. **ENRICH with 30-day timeline.**\n- **MET-RB (post-event implementation)** <-- MET-RB-7FS-006 (Lead or Gold Method) adds Russell's personal post-event implementation protocol with 7 steps. Existing DNA does not have this as a methodology. Could also be classified as NEW. **ENRICH / borderline NEW -- recommend adding as NEW.**\n\n---\n\n## DUPLICATES (skip)\n\n### Direct duplicates: 7\n\n1. **PHI-RB-7FS-002** (automated webinar as most reliable system) -- Covered broadly by PHI-RB-058 + existing webinar philosophy entries. The core claim is already captured. The 60-person call center origin story is new context but the philosophy is duplicate.\n2. **PHI-RB-7FS-007** (test small, reinvest) -- While I marked this as NEW above, the PHILOSOPHY is partially covered by the general funnel economics in PHI-RB-004/005. However the Vince James context is new enough to warrant NEW status. **Revised: keep as NEW.**\n3. **HEUR-RB-7FS-025** (replay at same timezone as registration) -- Covered implicitly in existing webinar replay sequences. Low incremental value. **SKIP.**\n4. **HEUR-RB-7FS-026** (guarantee EPC floor to new affiliates) -- The concept of generous affiliate compensation exists in PHI-RB-072. However the specific EPC guarantee mechanism is new. **Revised: keep as NEW.**\n5. **HEUR-RB-7FS-028** (SEO link diversity) -- Generic SEO principle, already implied in existing DNA's Skyscraper Technique and link building references. **SKIP.**\n6. **FW-RB-7FS-003** (Three Webinar Models: one-shot, automated, continuity) -- The 9 Core Funnels framework (line 809) already covers Auto-Webinar, Invisible Funnel, etc. The three-model distinction adds minor context. **SKIP as largely covered.**\n7. **FW-RB-7FS-004** (JV Email Sequence 5-email pre-launch) -- Covered by existing webinar indoctrination sequence entries (line 2360). The \"done-for-you copy for affiliates\" angle is partially covered in Dream 100 framework. **SKIP as largely covered.**\n\n### Net duplicates to skip: 4 (after revisions)\n\n---\n\n## CONFLICT FLAG\n\n**HEUR-RB-7FS-021** states registration page video of 60-75 sec with intro music increases conversion by 10-12%. However, existing **HEUR-RB (line 1298)** states: \"Videos on webinar registration pages ALWAYS destroy conversion. No video.\" This is a direct contradiction. The 7FS version comes from Kurt (media buying guest speaker) during a Q&A, while the existing entry comes from Russell's main Perfect Webinar teaching. **Resolution: Add the 7FS version tagged as \"Kurt (guest speaker)\" with a conflict note referencing existing HEUR-RB. Russell's own rule takes precedence; Kurt's finding may be context-specific (media buying traffic).**\n\n---\n\n## GUEST SPEAKER ELEMENTS\n\nThe following elements come from guest speakers, NOT Russell Brunson directly. They should be tagged accordingly:\n\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-021** (60-75 sec video + intro music) -- **Speaker: Kurt (media buying)**\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-027** ($2,500 spend -> $8,000 return example) -- **Speaker: Kurt (media buying)**\n- **HEUR-RB-7FS-017** ($300/month banner = 100+ opt-ins/day) -- appears to come from **general session**, RB presenting but referencing others\n- No elements extracted from Dave Van Hoos, Dustin Matthews, Luke Jayden, or Rachel Jackson despite them being listed as guest speakers -- the extraction correctly focused on RB's content.\n\n---\n\n## STATS\n\n| Metric | Count |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Total extracted** | **70** |\n| **New** | **48** (5 PHI + 7 MM + 24 HEUR + 8 FW + 4 MET) |\n| **Enrichments** | **12** (3 PHI + 2 MM + 2 HEUR + 3 FW + 2 MET) |\n| **Duplicates (skip)** | **4** (HEUR-7FS-025, HEUR-7FS-028, FW-7FS-003, FW-7FS-004) |\n| **Conflict flags** | **1** (HEUR-7FS-021 vs existing reg page video rule) |\n| **Guest speaker tags needed** | **2** (Kurt) |\n| **MET-RB-7FS-006 reclassified** | borderline ENRICH -> recommend NEW |\n\n### Post-Merge Projected DNA Stats\n\n| Layer | Current | + New | + Enriched | Projected Total |\n|-------|---------|-------|------------|-----------------|\n| L1 Philosophies | 86 | +5 | 3 enriched | 91 |\n| L2 Mental Models | 84 | +7 | 2 enriched | 91 |\n| L3 Heuristics | 157 | +24 | 2 enriched | 181 |\n| L4 Frameworks | 96 | +8 | 3 enriched | 104 |\n| L5 Methodologies | 47 | +4 | 2 enriched | 51 |\n| **TOTAL** | **470** | **+48** | **12 enriched** | **518** |\n\n---\n\nThis extraction is unusually rich in L3 Heuristics (24 new) because the 7 Figure Shortcut program is highly tactical and operational, with specific dollar amounts, benchmarks, and traffic channel specifics that do not exist in the more strategic/conceptual Secrets Masterclass DNA. The offline marketing content (classifieds, postcards, tear sheets, direct mail) is an entirely new domain not covered by any existing RB DNA.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>134827</total_tokens><tool_uses>25</tool_uses><duration_ms>243662</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\ad85028e5acbb258b.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-04T11:33:04.106281", "_id": "cae3a7e3"}
