{"type": "user_message", "content": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a1bcae2f50944c95a</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01AYfQAxmAjbYSoDmkDFmjty</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1bcae2f50944c95a.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract DNA IF Workshop\" completed</summary>\n<result>\n\nI have now read all 15 files. Let me deliver the complete DNA extraction.\n\n---\n\n# DNA EXTRACTION: Invisible Funnel Workshop (15 Sessions)\n\n## SESSION-BY-SESSION SUMMARY\n\n| Session | Speaker(s) | Core Topic |\n|---------|-----------|------------|\n| 1 | Russell Brunson | High-ticket selling via mini call centers, phone sales process, application funnels |\n| 2 | Russell Brunson | \"Inception\" - language patterns, NLP-style copywriting, embedded commands, inception loops |\n| 3 | Russell/Dagan | Webinar structure for Invisible Funnel, content webinar vs. pitch webinar, forced consumption |\n| 4 | John Alanis | Attractive Character deep-dive, email personality, daily emailing, creating a character persona |\n| 5 | John Alanis (cont.) | Colorful language, testing comedy/hooks on live audiences, backstory creation |\n| 6 | Dagan Smith / TJ Rohleder intro | Story selling introduction, TJ Rohleder's offer creation philosophy |\n| 7 | TJ Rohleder | Opportunity market psychology, offer stacking under pressure, relentless customer follow-up, beta tester offers |\n| 8 | Dagan Smith | Story Selling Architecture - the full \"Belief Installation\" framework, epiphany-driven stories |\n| 9 | Michael Hauge | Heroes Two Journeys - outer journey (6 stages, 5 turning points), story structure for marketing |\n| 10 | Michael Hauge (cont.) | Inner journey - wound/belief/fear/identity/essence framework, character arc |\n| 11 | Jonathan (videographer) | Video storytelling techniques, cinematic quality for marketing videos |\n| 12 | Dagan/Michael Hauge | Live story coaching - Russell's origin story rebuilt using Heroes Two Journeys framework |\n| 1", "metadata": {"session_id": "caf487f3-bf9b-403e-994e-d0f7fcf49a8d", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\caf487f3-bf9b-403e-994e-d0f7fcf49a8d.jsonl", "cwd": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\Downloads\\mega-brain-premium", "permission_mode": "acceptEdits", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a1bcae2f50944c95a</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01AYfQAxmAjbYSoDmkDFmjty</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1bcae2f50944c95a.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract DNA IF Workshop\" completed</summary>\n<result>\n\nI have now read all 15 files. Let me deliver the complete DNA extraction.\n\n---\n\n# DNA EXTRACTION: Invisible Funnel Workshop (15 Sessions)\n\n## SESSION-BY-SESSION SUMMARY\n\n| Session | Speaker(s) | Core Topic |\n|---------|-----------|------------|\n| 1 | Russell Brunson | High-ticket selling via mini call centers, phone sales process, application funnels |\n| 2 | Russell Brunson | \"Inception\" - language patterns, NLP-style copywriting, embedded commands, inception loops |\n| 3 | Russell/Dagan | Webinar structure for Invisible Funnel, content webinar vs. pitch webinar, forced consumption |\n| 4 | John Alanis | Attractive Character deep-dive, email personality, daily emailing, creating a character persona |\n| 5 | John Alanis (cont.) | Colorful language, testing comedy/hooks on live audiences, backstory creation |\n| 6 | Dagan Smith / TJ Rohleder intro | Story selling introduction, TJ Rohleder's offer creation philosophy |\n| 7 | TJ Rohleder | Opportunity market psychology, offer stacking under pressure, relentless customer follow-up, beta tester offers |\n| 8 | Dagan Smith | Story Selling Architecture - the full \"Belief Installation\" framework, epiphany-driven stories |\n| 9 | Michael Hauge | Heroes Two Journeys - outer journey (6 stages, 5 turning points), story structure for marketing |\n| 10 | Michael Hauge (cont.) | Inner journey - wound/belief/fear/identity/essence framework, character arc |\n| 11 | Jonathan (videographer) | Video storytelling techniques, cinematic quality for marketing videos |\n| 12 | Dagan/Michael Hauge | Live story coaching - Russell's origin story rebuilt using Heroes Two Journeys framework |\n| 13 | Michael Hauge (coaching) | Hot seat - live story critique and rebuild from ground up, structural feedback |\n| 14 | Russell Brunson | 7-Step Sales Process / Lifeline of a Lead, landing page split tests, conversion optimization |\n| 15 | Jimmy Davis | High-ticket phone closing from MLM, Glazer-Kennedy influenced selling, objection handling |\n\n---\n\n## L1 - PHILOSOPHIES (Core Beliefs)\n\n### NEW Elements\n\n**PHI-RB-301: The Inception Principle**\n> \"Your goal is not to convince someone. Your goal is to plant an idea so deeply that they believe it was their own idea.\"\n- Source: Session 2 (Russell on \"Inception\" presentation)\n\n**PHI-RB-302: Forced Consumption Philosophy**\n> \"I'm all about consumable, I want to force consumption. I want people to really enjoy it.\"\n- Source: Session 3 (Dagan, endorsed by Russell as core IF principle)\n\n**PHI-RB-303: Content Webinar Is An Experience, Not A Product**\n> \"The purpose of the content is just so they love it... it's not like we would think about a regular product. It's an experience.\"\n- Source: Session 3\n\n**PHI-RB-304: People Are Searching For A Miracle (Gene Schwartz)**\n> \"Gene Schwartz, arguably the greatest copywriter that ever lived, said everybody is looking for a miracle. They want to go to bed tonight and wake up tomorrow and their lives are totally transformed.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (TJ Rohleder, endorsed in Russell's ecosystem)\n\n**PHI-RB-305: Belief Installation Over Product Selling**\n> \"The impetus or emphasis in what I was doing was in the wrong place. I was telling the story to convince people why my product was so awesome. But all that matters is to help them have the belief that one simple idea will help them.\"\n- Source: Session 8 (Dagan, core IF philosophy)\n\n**PHI-RB-306: Identity Is More Frightening Than Death**\n> \"The death of one's identity is very often a lot more frightening than physical death. Hence, suicides.\"\n- Source: Session 10 (Michael Hauge)\n\n**PHI-RB-307: Passion Trumps Fear Every Time**\n> \"Passion trumps fear every time. If you need to confront their fear, the way you can help them overcome it is instilling them a passion.\"\n- Source: Session 10 (Michael Hauge)\n\n**PHI-RB-308: Safe vs. Fulfilled Choice**\n> \"The choice we are all given is: you can be safe and unfulfilled, or you can be fulfilled and scared shitless. Given a choice between safe and happy, we will pick safe most of the time.\"\n- Source: Session 10 (Michael Hauge)\n\n**PHI-RB-309: Flaws Build Trust**\n> \"People don't trust people that are too perfect. I like my favorite people that are just kind of flawed. That's one of the ways you earn trust - you reveal yourself to them.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (TJ Rohleder)\n\n**PHI-RB-310: If Refunds Are Too Low, You're Not Selling Hard Enough**\n> \"Brad Amton used to say: if your refunds are too low, you're not selling hard enough.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (TJ Rohleder)\n\n**PHI-RB-311: People Are Addicted To New**\n> \"People are addicted to new. There's nothing new under the sun, so we have to keep coming up with the appearance of new.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (TJ Rohleder)\n\n**PHI-RB-312: Internet Abundance Principle**\n> \"There's more than enough for everybody to have more than enough and there'd still be more than enough left over. Every time I make more money, it helps people that I don't even know make more money.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (Myron, at Russell's event)\n\n---\n\n## L2 - MENTAL MODELS (Thinking Frameworks)\n\n### NEW Elements\n\n**MM-RB-201: The Inception Loop Model**\n> Three layers of inception in copywriting: (1) Plant the idea, (2) Create emotional context so it feels like their own insight, (3) Let them \"discover\" the conclusion themselves.\n- Source: Session 2\n\n**MM-RB-202: Basketball Analogy for Idea Transfer**\n> \"If I have an idea, it's like a basketball. If I want it to be yours, I have to throw you the basketball. If I hold the ball, it's not yours. Case studies detach the idea from us - they throw the ball.\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**MM-RB-203: Poison Immunity Model (Sales Resistance)**\n> \"Insects build immunity to poison month to month. People have built the same kind of immunity/resistance to every sales message. You have to go over the top just to break through.\"\n- Source: Session 7 (TJ Rohleder)\n\n**MM-RB-204: The Hook In A Song Model**\n> \"Certain songs have a hook - it plays in your head for days. In creating offers, we're looking for something that sticks with people, an emotional hook they can't get out of their head.\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**MM-RB-205: Identity vs. Essence Model (Michael Hauge)**\n> Characters operate from Identity (false self/armor that keeps them safe) vs. Essence (true self/potential). The journey is from living in identity to living in essence. Inner conflict = tug of war between identity and essence.\n- Source: Sessions 9-10\n\n**MM-RB-206: Wound â†’ Belief â†’ Fear â†’ Identity Chain**\n> Every character/prospect has: a Wound (painful past experience) that creates a Belief (logical but inaccurate assumption about the world) that instills a Fear (avoidance of wound repetition) that creates an Identity (false self/armor).\n- Source: Session 10\n\n**MM-RB-207: Longing vs. Need**\n> \"Longing = deeply held desire they declare but won't go after. Need = something missing they won't even admit to themselves.\"\n- Source: Session 10\n\n**MM-RB-208: The Reflection Character Model**\n> The marketer/coach is the \"reflection character\" - helps with the outer journey while holding the person's feet to the fire on their inner transformation.\n- Source: Session 10\n\n**MM-RB-209: Lifeline of a Lead**\n> \"If a lead is coming into my business, what's the process I'm taking them through?\" - Thinking of the entire customer journey as a lifeline with 7 core steps.\n- Source: Session 14\n\n---\n\n## L3 - HEURISTICS (Rules of Thumb)\n\n### NEW Elements\n\n**HEUR-RB-301: 1-in-10 Recruiting Math**\n> \"About 1 out of every 10 people I recruited actually did something meaningful. And about 1 out of 10 of them did something significant at my level.\"\n- Source: Session 8 (Dagan's co-op story)\n\n**HEUR-RB-302: Co-op Cap at 100 People**\n> \"Never let more than 100 people get involved in one co-op because it's too hard to manage. Limit to 100, then pass it off.\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**HEUR-RB-303: $1 Qualifier Changes Everything**\n> \"Just asking for $1 changed everything. It's that emotional factor. We took the qualifier off thinking we'd get more leads, and we did, but the quality plummeted.\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**HEUR-RB-304: Test Offers on Best Customers First**\n> \"Test every offer to your best customers first. If your best customers don't get super excited about it, forget it. Then test down the segments.\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**HEUR-RB-305: 4-Level Customer Segmentation**\n> \"Segment your customer list into four different levels. Hardly anything works for the lowest tier, but keep testing.\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**HEUR-RB-306: Epiphany Must Be Simple**\n> \"It can't be 'I discovered the theory of relativity.' It's got to be like a co-op, one word. Something simple for them to get it and accept it.\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**HEUR-RB-307: 1,100 Registrations â†’ 500 Second Webinar**\n> \"I had 1,100 people register for the story webinar, and 500 registered for the second part. Just shortened the process and got bigger response than anything.\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**HEUR-RB-308: 5 Cave Points in Customer Journey**\n> The 5 turning points (at 10%, 25%, 50%, 75%, 90% of journey) are where customers are most likely to back out. Be prepared at each.\n- Source: Session 10 (Michael Hauge)\n\n**HEUR-RB-309: Story Chapters as Email Sequence**\n> \"I turned a sales letter into chapters. Give them this much, call it chapter one, put an opt-in box for chapter two. Each day release more. Day of launch was a damn good day.\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**HEUR-RB-310: Brainstorming Best Ideas Come at the Tail End**\n> \"That idea came at the tail end of a brainstorming session. We were already warmed up, engine fired up, talking about different ideas, and boom - the best idea came at the very end.\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n---\n\n## L4 - FRAMEWORKS (Structured Processes)\n\n### NEW Elements\n\n**FW-RB-401: Story Selling Architecture (Dagan's 12-Step Belief Installation)**\nFull framework for installing a belief through story:\n1. **High Drama** - Display impending doom / the wall\n2. **Display the Wall** - Show there's no way over/under/around/through\n3. **One Simple Thing** - A simple epiphany reveals a path (one word, one receipt, one idea)\n4. **New Possibilities Cascade** - More great ideas pour out from the one idea\n5. **Hero's Choice** - Hero must choose to act (display the choosing moment)\n6. **First Signs of Success** - Display the first tangible result\n7. **Rapid Growth** - Things continue to get better\n8. **Case Studies** - Detach idea from hero, prove it works for everyone (throw the basketball)\n9. **Hidden Benefits** - \"We all know X gives us A, B, C. But what people don't see is D, E, F\"\n10. **Objection Transformation** - Transform objections into positive reasons to say yes\n11. **Allude to Twist** - Hint at something even bigger (\"before I tell you...\")\n12. **Mistakes to Avoid** - Inoculate them (\"don't make the mistakes I made\")\n13. **Ultimate Solution Reveal** - The twist/tweak that changed everything\n14. **Bridge Pain to Invitation** - Remind of pain, connect to offer, invisible funnel proposition\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**FW-RB-402: Heroes Two Journeys (Michael Hauge - Outer Journey)**\n6 Stages + 5 Turning Points:\n- Stage 1: Setup (meet hero in everyday life)\n- Turning Point 1: Opportunity (10%)\n- Stage 2: New Situation (exploring/reacting)\n- Turning Point 2: Change of Plans (25%)\n- Stage 3: Progress (pursuing outer goal)\n- Turning Point 3: Point of No Return (50%)\n- Stage 4: Complications & Higher Stakes\n- Turning Point 4: Major Setback (75%)\n- Stage 5: Final Push (all-or-nothing)\n- Turning Point 5: Climax (90%)\n- Stage 6: Aftermath (show the after picture)\n- Source: Sessions 9-10\n\n**FW-RB-403: Heroes Two Journeys (Michael Hauge - Inner Journey)**\nCharacter Arc Framework:\n1. **Longing/Need** - What the hero deeply wants but won't pursue\n2. **Wound** - Painful past experience still running behavior\n3. **Belief** - Logical but inaccurate assumption from wound\n4. **Fear** - Avoidance of wound repetition\n5. **Identity** - False self/armor to stay safe\n6. **Essence** - True potential if they find courage\n- Journey: Identity â†’ Essence (must transform to win)\n- Rule: \"If the hero finds courage to live in essence, they win. If not, tragedy.\"\n- Source: Session 10\n\n**FW-RB-404: TJ Rohleder's 8-Step Offer Formula**\n1. Giant promises (hard to believe)\n2. Back them up with proof\n3. Tell the stories\n4. Use examples\n5. Better-than-no-risk guarantee (rewarded even if they refund)\n6. Relentless follow-up\n7. Salespeople for personal rapport\n8. Your personal story and vulnerability\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**FW-RB-405: Inception Writing Framework (Russell)**\nLanguage pattern layers for copywriting:\n1. **Embedded Commands** - Embed action-oriented commands within sentences\n2. **Presuppositions** - Frame statements that assume the desired conclusion\n3. **Nested Loops** - Open multiple story loops, close them in reverse order to maintain attention\n4. **Reframing** - Change the frame of reference for objections\n- Source: Session 2\n\n**FW-RB-406: Content Webinar Support Stack**\nSupporting elements to include in any IF content webinar:\n- Images, Stories, Demonstrations, Case Studies, Logic, News, History\n- Source: Session 3\n\n**FW-RB-407: 7-Step Sales Process (Lifeline of a Lead)**\nRussell's complete funnel optimization framework:\n1. Lead Capture / Entry Point\n2. Initial Offer (front-end)\n3. Upsell Sequence\n4. Follow-up Sequence\n5. Webinar / Presentation\n6. Application Process\n7. High-Ticket Close\n- Source: Session 14\n\n**FW-RB-408: Three Reasons Why I Sell This (Objection Handling)**\nMyron's framework for \"if it's so good why sell it\":\n1. Internet Abundance - helping you helps me\n2. Public Service Reframe - \"I was so angry it took me so long, I want to share with everyone\"\n3. Looking for Partners - \"I need people to do trainings for me, you could be one\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n---\n\n## L5 - METHODOLOGIES (Step-by-Step Implementations)\n\n### NEW Elements\n\n**MET-RB-501: Two-Part Invisible Funnel Webinar Method**\nStep-by-step implementation:\n1. Send emails with story hook (e.g., \"From bankruptcy to $286K/month - hear the full story\")\n2. Registration page = story teaser only, no product pitch\n3. Webinar 1: Tell the full story using Story Selling Architecture (FW-RB-401)\n4. End Webinar 1 with invitation to Webinar 2 (invisible funnel proposition: \"don't pay now, test it first\")\n5. Webinar 2: Deliver the content/method, make the IF offer\n6. Result: People pre-sold by belief installation, show up for content already wanting the product\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**MET-RB-502: Beta Tester Offer Method (TJ Rohleder)**\n1. Create the offer with full done-for-you service\n2. Frame as \"we need beta testers to get all the bugs out\"\n3. Explain \"the more websites/systems we have, the better we can test\"\n4. Include better-than-no-risk guarantee (keep everything even if refund)\n5. Give 30 days to decide in or out\n6. They keep all materials regardless\n7. Position as mutual profit: \"we profit by helping you profit\" (affiliate/JV structure)\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**MET-RB-503: Story Chapters Email Launch Sequence**\n1. Write full sales story using Story Selling Architecture\n2. Break into chapters (3-7 chapters)\n3. Day 1: Send Chapter 1 with opt-in box for \"get Chapter 2 before everyone else\"\n4. Days 2-6: Release one chapter per day\n5. Day of launch: Full offer revealed - \"biggest response ever\"\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**MET-RB-504: Perpetual Co-op Method (Dagan)**\n1. Put a lead capture page IN FRONT of the co-op advertising\n2. Manage the entire process for the team\n3. Build a master list from all co-op traffic\n4. Monetize master list by selling products/services\n5. Team grows, co-op budget grows, list grows - all perpetually\n6. Result: $10K+/month extra income + 5-10K new list members/month for free\n- Source: Session 8\n\n**MET-RB-505: High-Pressure Offer Stacking Under Duress**\nWhen facing a dead/resistant audience:\n1. Assess the crowd honestly (don't deny reality)\n2. Hold emergency team brainstorm session\n3. Stack the original offer with more and more value\n4. Let team members one-up each other (\"pissing championship\")\n5. Split the presentation: main pitch + team member explains all bonuses\n6. Result: \"Sold almost everybody in the room at $3-4K to people we were convinced wouldn't buy\"\n- Source: Session 7\n\n**MET-RB-506: Live Story Coaching Method (Michael Hauge)**\nProcess for rebuilding a marketing story:\n1. Ask questions first - understand the writer's vision (don't impose your own)\n2. Don't \"fix\" - rebuild from ground up\n3. Establish: What's the outer goal? What's the identity? What's the essence?\n4. Find the wound and belief\n5. Map the 5 turning points to the real story\n6. Ensure aftermath is included (the \"after picture\")\n7. Test: Does the hero transform from identity to essence?\n- Source: Session 13\n\n---\n\n## ENRICHMENTS TO EXISTING ELEMENTS\n\n| Existing Element | New Context from IF Workshop |\n|-----------------|----------------------------|\n| **Attractive Character** | Session 4-5 (John Alanis): Deep implementation detail - AC must have colorful language tested on live audiences like Marx Brothers; must send 2+ emails/day; vulnerability and flaws are key trust builders |\n| **Epiphany Bridge** | Session 8 provides the COMPLETE mechanism: the epiphany must be simple (one word/one receipt), must happen at moment of maximum peril (insurmountable object), and case studies \"throw the basketball\" to transfer ownership of the idea |\n| **The Stack** | Session 7 (TJ Rohleder): Real-world example of stacking under pressure at live event - team brainstormed for hours to create irresistible stack for resistant audience |\n| **Hook-Story-Offer** | Session 7: TJ's \"emotional hook\" concept (\"get paid thousands of times a day\") - find the one sentence buried in website copy and blow it up as headline |\n| **Value Ladder** | Session 1: Explicit mapping of IF into value ladder position - IF sits between free+shipping and high-ticket application |\n| **Three False Beliefs** | Session 8: Dagan's framework shows HOW to install new beliefs through story - the objection transformation step directly addresses false beliefs |\n| **Invisible Funnel (concept)** | Session 3/12: Live workshop reveals Russell's specific webinar outline structure, how he plans content to support the IF offer, images/stories/demos/case studies/logic/news/history as support elements |\n| **Perfect Webinar** | Session 3: Distinction between \"Dagan's way\" (recorded, polished) vs \"Russell's way\" (live, interactive) for IF webinars |\n\n---\n\n## KEY QUOTES (Verbatim)\n\n1. **Session 2 (Russell):** \"The whole concept of this presentation is Inception... how we structure words and language patterns that have been really, really effective.\"\n\n2. **Session 7 (TJ Rohleder):** \"If your refunds are too low, you're not selling hard enough.\"\n\n3. **Session 7 (TJ Rohleder):** \"As long as it sounds good - that's what he kept saying. Try to find those emotional hooks.\"\n\n4. **Session 8 (Dagan):** \"The impetus for where we put our thought is getting them to consume this concept so that they love it. And when they love it, our product is already sold.\"\n\n5. **Session 8 (Dagan):** \"If we tell a story, we go past trust and create identification.\"\n\n6. **Session 10 (Michael Hauge):** \"The inner journey for your hero is a journey from living in his identity to living in his essence.\"\n\n7. **Session 10 (Michael Hauge):** \"Beliefs that come from wounds are never accurate, but they are always logical.\"\n\n8. **Session 10 (Michael Hauge):** \"I'll do whatever it takes to achieve my goal. Just don't ask me to ___. Because that's just not me.\"\n\n9. **Session 7 (Myron):** \"There's more than enough for everybody to have more than enough and there'd still be more than enough left over.\"\n\n10. **Session 10 (Michael Hauge):** \"You can be safe and unfulfilled, or you can be fulfilled and scared shitless.\"\n\n---\n\n## EXTRACTION COUNTS\n\n| Category | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| **L1 - Philosophies (NEW)** | 12 |\n| **L2 - Mental Models (NEW)** | 9 |\n| **L3 - Heuristics (NEW)** | 10 |\n| **L4 - Frameworks (NEW)** | 8 |\n| **L5 - Methodologies (NEW)** | 6 |\n| **TOTAL NEW ELEMENTS** | **45** |\n| **Enrichments to Existing** | 8 |\n| **Key Quotes** | 10 |\n| **GRAND TOTAL** | **63 items extracted** |\n\n---\n\n## NOTES ON MULTI-SPEAKER CONTENT\n\nThis workshop is unique in the Russell Brunson corpus because it features multiple speakers at a live event. The primary DNA contributors are:\n\n- **Russell Brunson** (Sessions 1, 2, 3, 14) - Funnel architecture, inception copywriting, conversion optimization\n- **Dagan Smith** (Sessions 3, 6, 8, 12) - Story Selling Architecture (the 12-step belief installation framework) is the single most significant NEW extraction\n- **Michael Hauge** (Sessions 9, 10, 13) - Heroes Two Journeys (Identity vs. Essence) is a major framework Russell later incorporated deeply into Expert Secrets\n- **TJ Rohleder** (Session 7) - Offer psychology, customer addiction model, beta tester methodology\n- **John Alanis** (Sessions 4, 5) - Attractive Character implementation details\n- **Jimmy Davis** (Session 15) - High-ticket phone closing\n\nThe Michael Hauge content (Sessions 9-10) is particularly significant as it forms the foundational theory Russell later built the Epiphany Bridge and origin story frameworks upon in Expert Secrets. The Wound-Belief-Fear-Identity-Essence chain is directly traceable to Hauge's teaching at this workshop.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>130795</total_tokens><tool_uses>17</tool_uses><duration_ms>225813</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1bcae2f50944c95a.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-07T19:06:53.222881", "_id": "2e6c03ea"}
