{"type": "user_message", "content": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>aaed4b0c2a8b4ede2</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01KXcNMpK8Cx2sngDWtWdT3o</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\aaed4b0c2a8b4ede2.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract DNA from Black Box\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have enough content from all the files to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the complete YAML output.\n\nBased on thorough reading of all 11 Black Box transcription files, here is the complete DNA extraction organized by layer:\n\n---\n\n## L1 PHILOSOPHIES (PHI-RB-099 through PHI-RB-107)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-099\"\n        statement: \"The goal is not to sell people something - it's to get them to consume your content. If I can force you to consume the information, it'll change your life.\"\n        context: \"Explaining why the Invisible Funnel uses scheduled delivery rather than on-demand. Over 75% attendance rate on a 4-hour webinar proves forced consumption works.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-100\"\n        statement: \"Every business needs a value ladder - a front end, a middle, and a back end. When people hire me and pay me a ton of money to come into their business and look at it, it's the first thing I look at.\"\n        context: \"Core philosophy of the Black Box funnel. Buyer Magnet (front) â†’ Invisible Funnel (middle) â†’ Black Box/Application (back). The value ladder concept as the foundational lens for all business evaluation.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-101\"\n        statement: \"The people who get into my programs and say 'I gotta make mone", "metadata": {"session_id": "d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264.jsonl", "cwd": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\Downloads\\mega-brain-premium", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>aaed4b0c2a8b4ede2</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01KXcNMpK8Cx2sngDWtWdT3o</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\aaed4b0c2a8b4ede2.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract DNA from Black Box\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have enough content from all the files to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the complete YAML output.\n\nBased on thorough reading of all 11 Black Box transcription files, here is the complete DNA extraction organized by layer:\n\n---\n\n## L1 PHILOSOPHIES (PHI-RB-099 through PHI-RB-107)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-099\"\n        statement: \"The goal is not to sell people something - it's to get them to consume your content. If I can force you to consume the information, it'll change your life.\"\n        context: \"Explaining why the Invisible Funnel uses scheduled delivery rather than on-demand. Over 75% attendance rate on a 4-hour webinar proves forced consumption works.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-100\"\n        statement: \"Every business needs a value ladder - a front end, a middle, and a back end. When people hire me and pay me a ton of money to come into their business and look at it, it's the first thing I look at.\"\n        context: \"Core philosophy of the Black Box funnel. Buyer Magnet (front) â†’ Invisible Funnel (middle) â†’ Black Box/Application (back). The value ladder concept as the foundational lens for all business evaluation.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-101\"\n        statement: \"The people who get into my programs and say 'I gotta make money, I gotta make money' rarely end up making money. Those who say 'this marketing thing is cool, I've got to learn how to do this better' - those are the ones who become successful.\"\n        context: \"Black Box Introduction - distinguishing mindset of successful vs unsuccessful students. Focus on learning the process, not on immediate results.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-102\"\n        statement: \"Almost every product we've sold that has been a failure was because I thought I knew what people wanted, created it, tried to sell it, and nobody ever wanted it. When I asked people what they wanted and then created that, it always sold.\"\n        context: \"Module 1 - Philosophy behind the ASK Campaign methodology. Market research must precede product creation, never the reverse.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-103\"\n        statement: \"You can literally sell every single product in this funnel without actually having a real sales letter. There are basically two very simple scripts that you need - the Who-What-Why-How video and the case study video.\"\n        context: \"Module 3B - Philosophy that video scripts replace expensive copywriting. A good copywriter costs $15,000 plus 10% of sales. The Black Box process eliminates that need.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-104\"\n        statement: \"The quickest way to transform your business from wherever you're at to wherever you want to be is by implementing high-ticket things and then figuring out a good system to sell those high-ticket things.\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - explaining why the Black Box (high-ticket back end) is the ultimate business accelerator. Russell hit a ceiling selling $47-$97 products until he added high-ticket coaching.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-105\"\n        statement: \"People are more likely to consume and act upon your content if they have to schedule when they receive it. If I just put this on a download page, most of you guys would never have watched it.\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - explaining the psychology of scheduled delivery vs on-demand. The Invisible Funnel leverages commitment and scheduling to drive consumption.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-106\"\n        statement: \"It's almost impossible to sell something if you don't have some proof that you can sell it. A case study is very important - it's got to be about somebody else, not just you.\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - on the three prerequisites for an Invisible Funnel: case study (about someone else), instant result delivery, and a system. Case study must show third-party success.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-107\"\n        statement: \"Don't tie yourself so much to the results of what you're building right now as much as learning the process. After you've learned it and gone through it once, you'll be able to replicate it in any business you want.\"\n        context: \"Black Box Introduction - the process is the asset, not the specific funnel. Russell has launched dozens of businesses because he has the process down and can do it in his sleep.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n```\n\n## L2 MENTAL MODELS (MM-RB-083 through MM-RB-088)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MM-RB-083\"\n        name: \"The Value Ladder\"\n        description: \"Every business needs a progression from low-value/low-price to high-value/high-price. You take someone along a journey where each step delivers more value at a higher price. The bottom is free/cheap (buyer magnet), middle is medium (invisible funnel/courses), top is premium (coaching/done-for-you).\"\n        application: \"Map any business onto front end â†’ middle â†’ back end. The Black Box funnel IS a value ladder: Buyer Magnet ($0-$7) â†’ Invisible Funnel ($97-$497) â†’ Application/Coaching ($3k-$25k+). Diagnose business problems by finding gaps in the value ladder.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-084\"\n        name: \"The Dentist Value Ladder\"\n        description: \"A mental model for understanding ascension: free teeth cleaning â†’ upsell to whitening ($800) â†’ retainers ($3-4k) â†’ invisible braces ($10k). The customer is happy at each step because value increases proportionally. The free entry point creates the first transaction.\"\n        application: \"Use this analogy to explain value ladders to any business owner. Every industry has a natural progression from free/cheap to premium. The key is that each step provides genuine value, making the next step a natural decision.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-085\"\n        name: \"The 100-Visitor Split Test\"\n        description: \"Compare two funnels by sending 100 visitors to each. Traditional: 1% conversion at $197 = $197 revenue, 1 customer. Free+Shipping: 8% take free offer, 25% buy upsell = $394 revenue, 8 customers. Free+shipping produces 2x the revenue and 8x the customers from the same traffic.\"\n        application: \"Use this mental model to evaluate any funnel strategy. The counterintuitive insight: giving something away free with shipping generates more revenue AND more buyers than selling directly. Buyers are the real asset.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-086\"\n        name: \"The System Outline as Table of Contents\"\n        description: \"Your product/course is structured like a book's table of contents. Use the ASK Campaign to discover 5-7 categories of questions your market has, then organize them into a system outline. Each category becomes a module/chapter. The system outline IS the product.\"\n        application: \"After collecting survey responses, group them into 5-7 natural categories. Each category becomes a section of your system. This outline drives your buyer magnet content, invisible funnel teaching, and all downstream products.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-087\"\n        name: \"Karate Kid Learning Model\"\n        description: \"Like Mr. Miyagi teaching Daniel-san to wax the car and paint the fence, each step in the Black Box builds skills that only make sense when combined. Students must complete each step before moving to the next, trusting the process even when individual steps seem disconnected.\"\n        application: \"Do not skip ahead. Complete Module 1 fully before Module 2. The learning compounds and each piece serves the whole. Information overload comes from learning 5 steps at a time instead of focusing on just one.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-088\"\n        name: \"Supply and Demand Positioning\"\n        description: \"You cannot get on the phone with every single person on your list - you would die and your time would be worth nothing. It's all about supply and demand. You have to position yourself as an expert through an application process, not chase prospects.\"\n        application: \"Use application funnels to create scarcity and positioning. People must apply to work with you, not the other way around. This is the psychology behind the Black Box back end - the application process itself positions you as the expert.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n```\n\n## L3 HEURISTICS (HEUR-RB-132 through HEUR-RB-140)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-132\"\n        rule: \"Free+shipping buyer magnets convert at approximately 8% of visitors, compared to 1% for paid products. This yields 2x the revenue and 8x the customers from the same 100 visitors.\"\n        threshold: \"8% conversion rate for free+shipping offers vs 1% for direct-paid offers\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - the core math behind the buyer magnet strategy. 100 visitors â†’ 8 free+shipping buyers â†’ 25% upsell = $394 revenue vs 100 visitors â†’ 1 buyer at $197.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-133\"\n        rule: \"Invisible Funnel webinars achieve 85% live attendance rates and over 75% stay for the full 3-4 hours, compared to typical free webinars with declining attendance rates.\"\n        threshold: \"85% attendance rate for Invisible Funnel format\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - demonstrating the power of credit-card-down-but-not-charged model. People treat scheduled IF webinars seriously because they have skin in the game.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-134\"\n        rule: \"A good copywriter costs $15,000 plus usually 10% of your sales. The Black Box video script approach eliminates this cost entirely by using the Who-What-Why-How format.\"\n        threshold: \"$15,000 + 10% royalties for professional copywriting\"\n        context: \"Module 3B - justification for using simple video scripts instead of written sales letters. Video scripts are faster to produce and don't require copywriting expertise.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-135\"\n        rule: \"When building a Black Box funnel, block out at least 2 hours per day for the first 2-3 months. Complete each module before moving to the next - do not consume ahead of implementation.\"\n        threshold: \"2 hours/day minimum for 2-3 months\"\n        context: \"Black Box Introduction - implementation schedule recommendation. The people who fail are those who learn 5 steps at once without implementing.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-136\"\n        rule: \"The ASK Campaign survey should collect only ONE question: 'What is your number one question about [topic]?' Surveys with multiple questions produce too much data that's hard to make actionable.\"\n        threshold: \"1 question only in the survey\"\n        context: \"Module 1 - the ASK Campaign methodology. Single-question surveys are more actionable than multi-question ones. Group responses into 5-7 categories to create your system outline.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-137\"\n        rule: \"A survival company went from $30,000/month to over $800,000/month just by adding free+shipping buyer magnets (credit card knife, survival business card, perma-match) to the front of their funnel.\"\n        threshold: \"$30k/mo â†’ $800k/mo with buyer magnet addition\"\n        context: \"Overview webinar - case study of survival business using multiple free+shipping buyer magnets to build buyer lists and upsell products.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-138\"\n        rule: \"To sell high-ticket via application: don't bribe people too hard to apply or you get bad leads. The application process itself should filter and qualify. Use Dan Sullivan's 'three years from today' question.\"\n        threshold: \"Quality over quantity in application leads\"\n        context: \"Module 5 - application funnel philosophy. If you bribe people to apply really hard, you get a bunch of really bad leads that you don't want.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-139\"\n        rule: \"Over a 30-day email follow-up period after the Invisible Funnel, drip emails talking about what they learned and then pitch the application. People need to be at a certain spot in their life to apply for high-ticket.\"\n        threshold: \"30-day email drip sequence post-IF to application\"\n        context: \"Module 5 - not everyone applies immediately after the IF. A follow-up sequence catches the people who need more time and warming up.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-140\"\n        rule: \"If your ASK Campaign isn't getting enough responses, go to Facebook groups and forums in your niche. Join groups, post conversationally (not spammy), and look at most-viewed forum threads to discover what your market actually wants.\"\n        threshold: \"Use forums with 10,000+ active members for fastest results\"\n        context: \"Not Getting Answers to Your Survey module - three fallback methods when surveys don't generate enough responses: Facebook groups, niche forums, and researching most-popular forum threads.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Not_Getting_Answers_to_Your_Survey.txt\"\n```\n\n## L4 FRAMEWORKS (FW-RB-085 through FW-RB-093)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"FW-RB-085\"\n        name: \"Black Box 3-Step Ascension Funnel\"\n        components: \"Step 1: Buyer Magnet (free+shipping offer, $0-$7) â†’ Step 2: Invisible Funnel (premium webinar, credit card down but not charged, $97-$497) â†’ Step 3: Black Box Application (high-ticket coaching/services, $3k-$100k+). Each step ascends the customer up the value ladder.\"\n        application: \"Build all three components sequentially. The buyer magnet creates buyers, the IF delivers value and builds trust, the application sells high-ticket. Can mix and match - not everyone needs all three. Some go Buyer Magnet â†’ Black Box directly. Some go IF â†’ Black Box only.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-086\"\n        name: \"Who-What-Why-How Video Script (John Carlton Method)\"\n        components: \"Four questions answered in a short video: (1) Who are you? (2) What do you have? (3) Why do they need it? (4) How can they get it? Learned from copywriter John Carlton. Can sell any product in any niche with just these four answers.\"\n        application: \"Record a simple video answering these 4 questions for your buyer magnet sales page and for your IF registration page. Replaces expensive written sales copy. Keep it conversational - just answer the questions on camera, even with an iPhone.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-087\"\n        name: \"ASK Campaign Framework\"\n        components: \"(1) Create a fly-catcher page with one question: 'What is your #1 question about [topic]?' (2) Drive traffic to it. (3) Collect responses. (4) Group responses into 5-7 natural categories. (5) These categories become your System Outline / table of contents. (6) The system outline drives all your products.\"\n        application: \"Use before creating any product. The survey responses tell you exactly what to create, in what order, and using what language. Works in any market - potato guns, weight loss, internet marketing, survival. The outline becomes your buyer magnet content, your IF content, and your coaching curriculum.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-088\"\n        name: \"Invisible Funnel 3 Prerequisites\"\n        components: \"(1) Case Study - proof of someone ELSE (not you) getting results with your system. (2) Instant Result - something you can deliver during the webinar that creates immediate value. (3) A System - a structured process/methodology you teach. Without all three, the IF won't work.\"\n        application: \"Before running an IF, ensure you have: a third-party success story to use in your case study video, one actionable takeaway attendees get during the live event, and a clear step-by-step system you walk them through.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-089\"\n        name: \"Hot Market Indicators (8 Tests)\"\n        components: \"(1) Large number of people in the market. (2) Magazines exist about it (check magazine racks). (3) People are already spending money in this market. (4) People have credit cards/income. (5) Forums/communities exist with active members. (6) Other people are selling products in this niche. (7) Listen to other people's problems for product ideas. (8) Watch TV to spot markets being advertised to.\"\n        application: \"Before entering any market, run it through all 8 indicators. A market that fails on multiple indicators (like potato guns - small market, no high-ticket potential) can make some money but won't build a sustainable business. Use the Hot Markets Worksheet to score each indicator.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-090\"\n        name: \"Dan Sullivan's 'The Question' for Application Calls\"\n        components: \"Ask the prospect: 'If we were having this discussion three years from today and you were looking back over those three years, what would have had to happen in your life, both personally and professionally, for you to feel happy with your progress?' Based on Dan Sullivan's book 'The Question' (~50 pages).\"\n        application: \"Use this as the key question on application forms and during sales calls. It gets prospects to articulate their own goals and desired outcomes, making it easy to show how your coaching/program is the bridge to that future. The prospect sells themselves.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-091\"\n        name: \"Application Page Structure\"\n        components: \"(1) Tell me about your company - what are you selling? (2) What is currently working in your business? (3) Dan Sullivan's 'three years' question. (4) Phone number and Skype for international. (5) Email and website. Placed on IF thank-you page AND in 30-day follow-up email sequence.\"\n        application: \"The application page is positioned after the Invisible Funnel, either on the thank-you page or via follow-up emails. Don't bribe too hard to apply - quality over quantity. Applications are reviewed and a team member calls accepted applicants using a structured sales script.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-092\"\n        name: \"Free+Shipping Buyer Magnet Formula\"\n        components: \"(1) Create a physical or digital product (CD, DVD, book, MP3 player, credit card knife, etc.). (2) Offer it free, charge only shipping ($2-$7). (3) After purchase, upsell a related digital product or continuity program. (4) 25% of free+shipping buyers take the upsell. (5) The buyer list becomes the real asset.\"\n        application: \"The buyer magnet can be built in under an hour. It's the first step of the Black Box funnel. Most buyer magnets are CDs/DVDs of your system overview. The goal is not profit on this step - it's building a buyer list and covering ad costs. Use DiscDelivered.com for CD/DVD fulfillment.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-093\"\n        name: \"Forum Research Fallback Method\"\n        components: \"(1) Search Facebook for groups with 10k+ members in your niche. Join and post conversationally to get feedback. (2) Google '[your niche] + forum' and find forums with large membership. Post your question or research existing threads. (3) Sort forum threads by most views/replies to discover the most popular questions. (4) Use these questions to build your system outline even without running a formal ASK Campaign.\"\n        application: \"When your ASK Campaign survey isn't generating enough responses, use this three-step fallback. Forum threads sorted by most views reveal exactly what your market cares about. You can become an expert in any topic in a couple hours by reading the top forum threads and all their responses.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Not_Getting_Answers_to_Your_Survey.txt\"\n```\n\n## L5 METHODOLOGIES (MET-RB-048 through MET-RB-054)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MET-RB-048\"\n        name: \"Black Box Funnel Build-Out Methodology\"\n        steps: \"Week 1: Market research via ASK Campaign - identify hot market, collect questions, create system outline. Week 2: Build Buyer Magnet (free+shipping CD/DVD/book). Week 3: Build your Invisible Funnel system and content. Week 4+: Create video scripts (Who-What-Why-How + Case Study). Week 5+: Build application page and high-ticket back end. Then drive traffic via affiliates, solo ads, and Facebook.\"\n        application: \"Follow sequentially. Do not skip ahead. Complete each week's homework before moving to the next module. The entire funnel can be built in 8 weeks following this methodology.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-049\"\n        name: \"ASK Campaign Execution Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Create a fly-catcher page asking 'What is your #1 question about [topic]?' Step 2: Drive traffic (Facebook groups, forums, existing list, ads). Step 3: Collect responses (aim for 100+). Step 4: Read every response and identify keyword patterns. Step 5: Group responses into 5-7 natural categories. Step 6: Create your System Outline from these categories. Step 7: This outline becomes the table of contents for all your products.\"\n        application: \"The ASK Campaign is the foundation of the entire Black Box. Without it, you're guessing what the market wants. Use SurveyMonkey or similar tool. Watch for patterns in keywords across responses. The system outline drives the buyer magnet, IF content, and coaching curriculum.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_1.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-050\"\n        name: \"Case Study + Magic Bullet Sales Video Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Find someone who got results with your system (not you - a third party). Step 2: Create a short case study video showing their results and the system that produced them. Step 3: Use case study video to drive IF registrations ('come see how we did this'). Step 4: At the end of IF, present the Magic Bullet - your done-with-you or done-for-you offer that makes results faster/easier. Step 5: Magic Bullet upsell leads to the application page.\"\n        application: \"The case study video is the entry point to the funnel. The magic bullet is the upsell at the end of the IF. Both must be genuine and results-based. Record case study with your iPhone - it doesn't need to be polished.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-051\"\n        name: \"Who-What-Why-How Video Recording Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Write out answers to four questions about your product - Who are you? What do you have? Why do they need it? How can they get it? Step 2: Record yourself answering these questions on camera (iPhone is fine). Step 3: Keep it conversational, not scripted. Step 4: Place this video on your buyer magnet sales page and IF registration page. Step 5: This single video replaces a traditional written sales letter.\"\n        application: \"Learned from copywriter John Carlton. Works for any product in any niche. You can rattle off these four answers for any product and it becomes a complete sales message. No copywriting skills required.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-052\"\n        name: \"Application Funnel Close Process\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: After IF, present application on thank-you page. Step 2: Run 30-day email drip to non-applicants with value content and application CTA. Step 3: Collect application with Dan Sullivan's Question + business details. Step 4: Review applications - accept qualified leads only. Step 5: Have team member (not you) call accepted applicants using structured script. Step 6: On the call, discuss their goals (from the Question), diagnose their problems, present your coaching as the solution. Step 7: Close or redirect to lower-ticket alternative.\"\n        application: \"The homework page and IF warm prospects up so by the time they're on the phone, they already trust you. Don't get on the phone with everyone - supply and demand positioning. If not accepted, send email with suggestions for what to do next.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-053\"\n        name: \"Invisible Funnel Execution Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Create case study video showing third-party results. Step 2: Registration page: 'Get started for $0 - enter credit card, won't be charged until after the training.' Step 3: Deliver 2-4 hour premium training webinar (live or automated). Step 4: During webinar, deliver instant results and teach your system. Step 5: At the end, say 'if this was valuable, we'll bill the agreed price; if not, email us before [date] and we won't charge.' Step 6: Present Magic Bullet upsell and application for high-ticket.\"\n        application: \"The zero-dollar entry with credit card guarantees high attendance (85%+) and consumption. Automate with software that lets people pick their date/time for the replay. The more often you do IF events, the higher percentage of people will pay because trust compounds.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-054\"\n        name: \"Forum Research Rapid Expert Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Google '[your niche] + forum'. Step 2: Find forums with 10,000+ active members. Step 3: Sort threads by most views/replies. Step 4: Read the top 10-20 most popular threads and ALL their responses. Step 5: Extract the most common questions and pain points. Step 6: Within 2 hours, you will know every important question in the niche and become a functional expert. Step 7: Feed these questions into your System Outline.\"\n        application: \"Works when ASK Campaign surveys aren't generating enough responses. Also works for entering a new market where you're not yet an expert. Example: reading 170 responses about WordPress plugins makes you an expert in that topic. The market literally teaches you what it needs.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Not_Getting_Answers_to_Your_Survey.txt\"\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary of extraction:**\n\n| Layer | IDs Used | Count |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| L1 PHILOSOPHIES | PHI-RB-099 through PHI-RB-107 | 9 |\n| L2 MENTAL MODELS | MM-RB-083 through MM-RB-088 | 6 |\n| L3 HEURISTICS | HEUR-RB-132 through HEUR-RB-140 | 9 |\n| L4 FRAMEWORKS | FW-RB-085 through FW-RB-093 | 9 |\n| L5 METHODOLOGIES | MET-RB-048 through MET-RB-054 | 7 |\n| **TOTAL** | | **40 elements** |\n\nAll elements are sourced from the 11 Black Box files in `knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/`. Key concepts covered: Black Box 3-Step Ascension, Value Ladder, 100-Visitor Split Test (2x revenue/8x customers), Who-What-Why-How Script (John Carlton), 8 Hot Market Indicators, ASK Campaign, Dan Sullivan's \"The Question\", IF 85% attendance, Free+Shipping at 8% conversion, Application Funnel Close Process, Case Study + Magic Bullet, and Forum Research Fallback Method.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>124067</total_tokens><tool_uses>65</tool_uses><duration_ms>366803</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\aaed4b0c2a8b4ede2.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-07T19:24:58.140006", "_id": "a617680e"}
{"type": "response", "preview": "[response complete]", "_timestamp": "2026-03-07T19:33:08.914822", "_id": "eef7653f"}
{"type": "user_message", "content": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a4fcc8117f50967f7</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_011RYkEneKVCGobrST5vKduc</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a4fcc8117f50967f7.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract Agent-B DNA elements\" completed</summary>\n<result>I now have enough content from all 15 sessions to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the YAML output based on the actual content from these transcriptions.\n\nHere is the extracted DNA:\n\n---\n\n## L1 - PHILOSOPHIES (PHI-RB-087 to PHI-RB-098)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-087\"\n        statement: \"People don't buy products, they buy beliefs. If you can help a prospect have a new belief through story, the product is already sold before you even present it.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on story selling architecture\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-088\"\n        statement: \"The impetus for selling should not be on convincing people why your product is awesome. All that matters is helping them have the belief that one simple idea will help them. When they love the idea, your product is already sold.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith reframing the emphasis from product to belief installation\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-089\"\n        statement: \"Everybody is looking for a miracle. They want to go to bed tonight and wake up tomorrow with their lives totally transformed. From an emotional standpoint, which is the core of where everybody buys, they want to believe so much.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funn", "metadata": {"session_id": "d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264.jsonl", "cwd": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\Downloads\\mega-brain-premium", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a4fcc8117f50967f7</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_011RYkEneKVCGobrST5vKduc</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a4fcc8117f50967f7.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract Agent-B DNA elements\" completed</summary>\n<result>I now have enough content from all 15 sessions to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the YAML output based on the actual content from these transcriptions.\n\nHere is the extracted DNA:\n\n---\n\n## L1 - PHILOSOPHIES (PHI-RB-087 to PHI-RB-098)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-087\"\n        statement: \"People don't buy products, they buy beliefs. If you can help a prospect have a new belief through story, the product is already sold before you even present it.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on story selling architecture\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-088\"\n        statement: \"The impetus for selling should not be on convincing people why your product is awesome. All that matters is helping them have the belief that one simple idea will help them. When they love the idea, your product is already sold.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith reframing the emphasis from product to belief installation\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-089\"\n        statement: \"Everybody is looking for a miracle. They want to go to bed tonight and wake up tomorrow with their lives totally transformed. From an emotional standpoint, which is the core of where everybody buys, they want to believe so much.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on the psychology of the opportunity market, citing Gene Schwartz\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-090\"\n        statement: \"You can never own your customers. Even though you own the list, they're going to do business with everybody else too. But you can consciously be in front of them more often, realizing that all you need is small groups to buy from you on a regular basis to make a nice profit.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on customer relationship reality\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-091\"\n        statement: \"People don't trust people that are too perfect. The people with gleaming white teeth and every hair in place - I just don't trust them. It's the people that are kind of flawed and show you they're a little flawed. That's one of the ways you earn trust - you reveal yourself to them and that endears people to you.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on vulnerability as trust mechanism\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-092\"\n        statement: \"When you tell a story, you go past trust and create identification. The audience isn't themselves anymore - they are there experiencing the story with the hero. Stories create identification, not just trust.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on why stories are more powerful than traditional persuasion\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-093\"\n        statement: \"Passion trumps fear every time. If you need to confront your prospect's fear, the way you help them overcome it is by instilling in them a passion. Keep showing them the aftermath - the new life they're going to live.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Michael Hauge on the inner journey and overcoming identity resistance\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-094\"\n        statement: \"Given a choice between safe and happy, people will pick safe most of the time. The choice we are all given is: you can be safe and unfulfilled, or you can be fulfilled and scared shitless.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Michael Hauge on identity vs essence and why prospects resist transformation\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-095\"\n        statement: \"Don't be afraid to go over the top with your promises. People have built an immunity to sales messages like insects build immunity to poison. You have to go over the top just to break through that resistance.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on overcoming sales resistance with bold promises backed by proof and guarantees\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-096\"\n        statement: \"It's better to replace a bad idea with a good one than to try to suppress it or get rid of it. When you're in a bad situation, consume personal development to replace negative thoughts with positive ones.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith's personal story about listening to CDs during difficult times\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-097\"\n        statement: \"The purpose of the content webinar in an invisible funnel is not like a regular product pitch. It's an experience. They should feel like they leave with a lot of value. It's not about the hard sell - it's about making them love it.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on the purpose of content in the invisible funnel model\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_3.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-098\"\n        statement: \"If your refunds are too low, you're not selling hard enough. Having a better-than-no-risk guarantee eliminates all the risk, and on top of that, you're rewarding them even if they get their money back.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder quoting Brad Amton on refund philosophy and better-than-risk-free guarantees\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n```\n\n## L2 - MENTAL MODELS (MM-RB-074 to MM-RB-082)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MM-RB-074\"\n        name: \"Belief Installation Model\"\n        description: \"The goal of marketing is not to convince people your product is great, but to install a single simple belief that leads them to conclude they need what you offer. When the belief is accepted, the product sells itself.\"\n        application: \"Structure all content webinars and story selling around installing one core belief rather than listing product features. The product becomes the natural conclusion of the belief.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-075\"\n        name: \"Identity vs Essence Framework\"\n        description: \"Every person has an identity (false self created for emotional protection) and an essence (their true potential self). The journey from identity to essence is what creates transformation. People resist because their identity feels like death to abandon.\"\n        application: \"When selling transformation, understand that prospects' resistance is not about price or logistics - it's about the terror of abandoning who they believe they are. Marketing must show the aftermath of living in essence to make it worth the fear.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-076\"\n        name: \"Basketball Throw Analogy for Idea Ownership\"\n        description: \"If you hold the basketball (idea), it's yours. To make it the prospect's, you must throw it to them. Case studies are how you detach the idea from yourself so they can catch and own it. Without case studies they think 'good for you, won't work for me.'\"\n        application: \"After presenting your epiphany story, immediately stack case studies of OTHER people who got the same result to transfer ownership of the idea from you to the prospect.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-077\"\n        name: \"Wound-Belief-Fear-Identity Chain\"\n        description: \"A painful past experience (wound) creates a belief about how the world works, which instills a fear, which causes the creation of a false identity (armor) to protect against that fear. Understanding this chain in your audience reveals why they resist action.\"\n        application: \"When creating customer avatars or stories, map the wound-belief-fear-identity chain for your target audience. Your marketing must address the identity they're hiding behind and show them the path to their essence.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-078\"\n        name: \"Insect Immunity Analogy\"\n        description: \"Just like insects build immunity to poison so pest control companies must change their formula each month, consumers build immunity to sales messages. You must constantly go over the top and find new hooks to break through increasing resistance.\"\n        application: \"Constantly test new angles, hooks, and emotional triggers. What worked last month may not break through this month. Keep escalating the boldness of promises while backing them with proof.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-079\"\n        name: \"Song Hook Principle for Offers\"\n        description: \"Great offers should work like a song hook - an emotional trigger that sticks in people's heads and they can't get rid of. Find the one sentence buried in your offer that really excites people and blow it up into your headline.\"\n        application: \"When creating offers, look for the one emotionally sticky phrase or concept buried in the details. Extract it and make it the centerpiece of all marketing. Example: 'get paid thousands of times a day' was buried in website copy and became the main hook.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-080\"\n        name: \"Reflection Character Model\"\n        description: \"In stories and in marketing, you must serve as the 'reflection character' - the sidekick who helps with the outer journey (practical goals) while simultaneously forcing the hero to face their inner truth and overcome their identity resistance.\"\n        application: \"Position yourself as both helpful guide AND the person who calls out their excuses. Support their practical goals while holding their feet to the fire about what's really stopping them.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-081\"\n        name: \"Lifeline of a Lead\"\n        description: \"View every lead as having a complete lifecycle or 'lifeline' through your business. Most people only think about traffic, but the real focus should be on every step: opt-in, first touchpoint, indoctrination, content delivery, offer, upsell, follow-up, and ascension.\"\n        application: \"Map out the complete journey a lead takes from first contact through highest-ticket purchase. Optimize each step of the lifeline, not just the front-end acquisition.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_14.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-082\"\n        name: \"Internet Abundance Principle\"\n        description: \"There's more than enough for everybody to have more than enough and there'd still be more than enough left over. Helping others make money helps you make money. Use this to overcome the 'if it's so good why are you selling it' objection.\"\n        application: \"When facing skepticism about why you'd share a profitable system, frame it with three rebuttals: 1) Internet abundance - helping them profit helps you profit, 2) Personal mission to share after struggling, 3) You're looking for people to do your trainings.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n```\n\n## L3 - HEURISTICS (HEUR-RB-122 to HEUR-RB-131)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-122\"\n        rule: \"The epiphany in your story must be something SIMPLE - one word, one receipt, one sentence. If the idea is complex, the audience won't believe they can replicate the result.\"\n        threshold: \"One word or one simple concept maximum for the epiphany moment\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on the insurmountable object and epiphany structure in story selling\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-123\"\n        rule: \"Test every new offer to your best customers first as guinea pigs. If your best customers don't get super excited about it, forget it. Then test to your general customer base, then to cold prospects.\"\n        threshold: \"Best customers first > general customers > cold list. If best customers don't respond, kill the offer.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on segmented offer testing and customer list hierarchy\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-124\"\n        rule: \"Segment your customer list into at least 4 levels based on purchase behavior. The top segment buys almost anything, the bottom segment (just the initial small purchase) barely responds to anything. Keep testing to all segments but expect dramatically different response rates.\"\n        threshold: \"Minimum 4 segments by purchase depth\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on customer list segmentation from 25 years experience\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-125\"\n        rule: \"A $1 qualifier on a free offer changes everything about lead quality. Even though $1 is nothing financially, the emotional factor of committing any amount of money dramatically filters the list.\"\n        threshold: \"$1 minimum qualifier to separate serious prospects from tire-kickers\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder citing example from Russ Von Holtscher's Profit Ideas company\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-126\"\n        rule: \"In a two-part story selling webinar, if 1,100 register for Part 1 (the story), expect approximately 500 (45%) to register for Part 2 (the invisible funnel content). They absolutely show up for the second one because you got them excited in Part 1.\"\n        threshold: \"~45% conversion from story webinar Part 1 to content webinar Part 2\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith sharing actual stats from list publisher profits launch\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-127\"\n        rule: \"In network marketing or team-based businesses, approximately 1 out of every 10 people you recruit will do something meaningful, and about 1 out of 10 of those will do something significant at your level. This math gives certainty for planning lead generation needs.\"\n        threshold: \"10% meaningful action rate, 1% significant performer rate from total recruits\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith sharing his perpetual duplication story math\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-128\"\n        rule: \"The five turning points in any customer journey (10%, 25%, 50%, 75%, 90%) are exactly where they are most likely to back out. If you know these points in advance, you can prepare counter-measures.\"\n        threshold: \"5 critical dropout points mapped to the Heroes Two Journeys story structure\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Michael Hauge on applying story structure to customer journey dropout points\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-129\"\n        rule: \"When you're stuck with a 'dead crowd' that won't buy, keep stacking the offer with more and more value until the promise is so overwhelming they can't say no. Use competitive brainstorming among your team to keep topping each other's ideas.\"\n        threshold: \"Stack until you sell almost everybody in the room, even problem customers\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder's San Diego seminar story where 'dead crowd' bought $3-4K offer after massive stacking\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-130\"\n        rule: \"Support your invisible funnel content webinar offer with images, stories, demonstrations, case studies, logic, news, and history. These elements make the webinar an experience, not a pitch.\"\n        threshold: \"Minimum: images + stories + demonstrations + case studies + logic in every content webinar\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - Dagan Smith on structuring invisible funnel content webinars\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_3.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-131\"\n        rule: \"Most people don't promote to their existing customers frequently enough. If you're not pitching them every week with something new or a new angle, your competitors are. People are addicted to new - create the appearance of new constantly.\"\n        threshold: \"Minimum weekly contact with existing customers with new offers, angles, or stories\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel Workshop - TJ Rohleder on relentless customer contact frequency\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n```\n\n## L4 - FRAMEWORKS (FW-RB-077 to FW-RB-084)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"FW-RB-077\"\n        name: \"Story Selling Architecture (Dagan Smith)\"\n        components: \"1) High Drama (display a wall - insurmountable obstacle), 2) One Simple Epiphany (one word/idea that changes everything), 3) New Possibilities Cascade (all the ideas that flow from the epiphany), 4) Hero's Choice (choose to act despite fear), 5) First Signs of Success, 6) Rapid Growth, 7) Case Studies (detach idea from you - throw the basketball), 8) Hidden Benefits (what people don't see beyond obvious), 9) Objection Transformation (turn objections into reasons to say yes), 10) Allude to Twist (something bigger you haven't revealed), 11) Mistake Inoculation (protect them from your mistakes), 12) Ultimate Solution Reveal (the twist that makes it even better), 13) Pain Bridge (remind of pain of inaction), 14) Invitation (invisible funnel proposition)\"\n        application: \"Use this 14-step architecture to structure content webinars, sales letters, and email sequences. The architecture creates belief in one simple idea, proves it works for everyone, then makes the product the natural conclusion.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-078\"\n        name: \"Heroes Two Journeys (Michael Hauge)\"\n        components: \"Outer Journey (visible goal pursuit): Setup > Opportunity (10%) > Change of Plans (25%) > Point of No Return (50%) > Major Setback (75%) > Climax (90-99%) > Aftermath. Inner Journey (identity to essence transformation): Living in Identity > Glimpse of Essence > Vacillation between Identity and Essence > Full Commitment to Essence > Retreat to Identity after Setback > Final Push > Full Essence Achievement\"\n        application: \"Every marketing story must have both an outer journey (the visible goal and obstacles) AND an inner journey (the emotional transformation from fear to courage, from identity to essence). The two journeys intertwine at the same structural turning points.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_9.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-079\"\n        name: \"TJ Rohleder's 8-Step Offer Formula\"\n        components: \"1) Giant Promises (huge, almost hard to believe), 2) Proof (back up promises with evidence), 3) Stories and Examples (your story + customer stories), 4) Premium Pricing (make it special, just for them), 5) Better-Than-No-Risk Guarantee (they keep everything even if they refund), 6) Relentless Follow-Up (salespeople, teleseminars, webinars), 7) Emotional Hook (the one sticky phrase they can't get out of their head), 8) Your Story and Vulnerability (reveal your flaws, build trust through authenticity)\"\n        application: \"Apply all 8 elements to every high-ticket offer. The formula works from $9 front-end offers all the way to $3,000+ back-end offers. The key differentiator is the better-than-no-risk guarantee and the emotional hook.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-080\"\n        name: \"Attractive Character Email Framework (John Alanis)\"\n        components: \"1) Create an Attractive Character persona to speak from, 2) Use colorful language (test and discard what doesn't work, keep what does - like Marx Brothers testing comedy), 3) Send two emails per day from the character's voice, 4) Share personal stories and flaws to build identification, 5) Maintain consistent voice and vocabulary across all communications\"\n        application: \"Build a persona that people tune in to read HOW you write as much as WHAT you write. Test colorful language sparingly at first, keep what resonates. People respond to characters, not faceless brands. John Alanis' implementation doubled then quadrupled Dagan Smith's business.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_4.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-081\"\n        name: \"Beta Tester Method (TJ Rohleder)\"\n        components: \"1) Create a 'reason why' offer framed as needing beta testers, 2) Frame it as: 'we need beta testers to get all the bugs out,' 3) Explain: 'the more websites/systems we have, the better we can test,' 4) Use done-for-you elements where you profit by helping them profit, 5) Include better-than-no-risk guarantee (keep everything even if refund), 6) Works for 15+ years without competitors copying it\"\n        application: \"Frame your offer launch as a beta test. This gives a legitimate 'reason why' for the offer, reduces skepticism, and creates urgency. Combined with done-for-you elements and affiliate structures where 'the more we help you make, the more we make.' TJ has mailed millions of these pieces over 17 years.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-082\"\n        name: \"Inception Language Pattern Framework\"\n        components: \"1) Identify the belief you want to install, 2) Structure words and language patterns that plant the idea without direct persuasion, 3) Use stories as delivery vehicle for inception (the audience doesn't realize the belief is being installed), 4) Layer multiple language patterns to reinforce the core belief, 5) Let the audience arrive at the conclusion themselves\"\n        application: \"Named after the movie Inception. Instead of directly persuading, use language patterns and stories to plant ideas that the prospect believes they came up with themselves. Russell's approach to copy: not copywriting per se, but structuring words and language patterns for inception-style belief installation.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_2.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-083\"\n        name: \"Three Objection Killers for 'Why Are You Selling This?'\"\n        components: \"1) Internet Abundance: 'There's more than enough for everybody - helping you make money helps me make money' (analogy: $50 junk car vs $100K Mercedes generating revenue for entire ecosystem), 2) Personal Mission: 'It took me so long to figure out how to get rich, I was so angry I decided to share from the rooftops as a public service,' 3) Scaling Through Others: 'My business is growing so fast, I'm looking for other people to do my trainings for me - I don't want to travel every weekend at 52'\"\n        application: \"Use all three reasons when prospects ask 'if this is so good, why sell it to me instead of keeping it for yourself?' Each reason reframes their skepticism from a different angle. Combined, they dismantle the objection completely.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-084\"\n        name: \"Chapter-Based Sales Letter Launch\"\n        components: \"1) Write your sales story as a narrative, not a traditional sales letter, 2) Break the story into chapters, 3) Release one chapter at a time to your list (daily), 4) Add an opt-in box at end of each chapter: 'opt in to get chapter X before everyone else,' 5) Build anticipation through the story arc, 6) On launch day, the audience is primed and eager to buy\"\n        application: \"Instead of sending a long sales letter all at once, serialize it into chapters released daily. Each chapter builds anticipation and the opt-in creates commitment escalation. Dagan used this early in his career as one of his best promotions but never repeated it - 'I don't know why I never did it again, it was dumb.'\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n```\n\n## L5 - METHODOLOGIES (MET-RB-042 to MET-RB-047)\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MET-RB-042\"\n        name: \"Two-Part Story Selling Webinar Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Send short emails with a compelling story hook for registration (e.g., 'From bankruptcy and addiction to $286,000/month - hear the full story for the first time'). Step 2: Part 1 Webinar - Tell the full story using the Story Selling Architecture (high drama > epiphany > proof > hidden benefits > objection transformation > allude to twist). Step 3: At the end of Part 1, make the invisible funnel proposition ('Tomorrow I'll share how to do this live - don't give me a dime now, put me to the test'). Step 4: Part 2 Webinar - Deliver the content/training. Step 5: Close with invisible funnel offer.\"\n        application: \"Use when launching any product or service. Part 1 creates the belief and excitement through story. Part 2 delivers the content. The two-part structure gets higher conversion than cramming story + content + close into one session. 1,100 registered for Part 1 > 500 registered for Part 2 in Dagan's case.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-043\"\n        name: \"Active Emotion Writing Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Identify the key emotion your hero feels at each point in the story. Step 2: Do NOT write the emotion passively (e.g., 'I was depressed'). Step 3: Instead, bring the reader INTO the experience by describing three layers: a) Mental thoughts ('All I could think was, why me?'), b) Physical sensations ('My heart sunk,' 'my hands got cold, my mouth went dry'), c) The experience itself ('When I looked at the piece of paper and it said...'). Step 4: Journal about what emotions physically feel like to build your vocabulary of physical sensations. Step 5: Apply this active emotional writing to every key turning point in your story.\"\n        application: \"Use whenever writing sales copy, emails, or video scripts that involve emotional moments. Passive emotion ('I was excited') creates no identification. Active emotion ('My hands got cold, my mouth went dry, I started tingling all over') creates full identification and transportation into the experience.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-044\"\n        name: \"Inner Journey Diagnostic Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Ask 'What does my hero long for?' (a deeply held desire they're too afraid to pursue). Step 2: Ask 'What was my hero's wound?' (a painful past experience they believe they've left behind but still determines their behavior). Step 3: Ask 'What is my hero's belief?' (the conclusion they drew from the wound about how the world works - always logical but never accurate). Step 4: Ask 'What is my hero's fear?' (what they're afraid of based on the belief). Step 5: Ask 'What is my hero's identity?' (the false self created to protect against the fear). Step 6: Ask 'What is my hero's essence?' (who they would be if they could strip away all the armor). Step 7: Fill in the blank: 'I'll do whatever it takes to achieve my goal. Just don't ask me to ___ because that's just not me.' The blank reveals their identity resistance.\"\n        application: \"Use before creating any marketing story or customer avatar. Map the wound-belief-fear-identity-essence chain for your target customer. This reveals the real reason they resist buying or taking action. The 'fill in the blank' exercise is especially powerful for identifying what's REALLY stopping your prospects.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_10.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-045\"\n        name: \"Story Content Mapping Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Brain-dump ALL content ideas related to your core belief/idea. Step 2: List all possible objections your audience will have. Step 3: List all benefits (obvious and hidden). Step 4: For each piece of content, tag it with where it fits in the Story Selling Architecture (HB = hidden benefit, regular benefit, case study, mistake, etc.). Step 5: Identify which benefits are 'hidden' - frame as 'Everyone knows X, but what most people don't see is Y.' Step 6: Organize all tagged content into the story flow. Step 7: Create a visual map showing the hero's journey story with episodes/moments attached to each structural point.\"\n        application: \"Use when building out any story-based presentation or sales webinar. This method ensures no good content is wasted and every piece of content is strategically placed in the architecture for maximum impact. The visual map 'might look crazy but this is what it looks like when I have it all in order.'\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_8.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-046\"\n        name: \"Competitive Offer Stacking Method\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Start with your base offer. Step 2: Gather your team (marketing, sales, key people) in a brainstorming session. Step 3: Challenge everyone: 'How can we give them MORE?' Step 4: Let it become a 'pissing championship' where each person tries to top the previous idea. Step 5: Keep stacking until even you can't keep track of everything being offered. Step 6: In the presentation, present what you can, then hand off to your marketing person to explain the rest. Step 7: Use this especially when the audience seems resistant or 'dead.'\"\n        application: \"When facing a tough crowd or needing to close at high ticket, use competitive team brainstorming to stack the offer beyond what anyone would expect. TJ Rohleder sold almost everybody in a 'dead' room at $3-4K per person using this method after his 20-year veteran told him 'this crowd won't buy anything.'\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_7.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-047\"\n        name: \"Story Coaching Rebuild Method (Michael Hauge)\"\n        steps: \"Step 1: Don't try to 'fix' the story by moving pieces around - rebuild from the ground up. Step 2: Ask questions first to understand the creator's vision (don't impose your own). Step 3: Establish the visible goal (must be specific, clear, and something you can picture). Step 4: Map the outer journey turning points (opportunity, change of plans, point of no return, major setback, climax). Step 5: Map the inner journey (wound, belief, fear, identity, essence). Step 6: Ensure the aftermath is included - show the 'after picture' of the new life, not just the climax achievement. Step 7: Intertwine outer and inner journeys at matching turning points.\"\n        application: \"Use when coaching others (or yourself) on their origin story or sales story. The key insight is that most stories fail because they lack the aftermath ('and then she made a million dollars' is not enough - describe the NEW LIFE) and because they skip the inner journey transformation.\"\n        module_sources: [IF-WORKSHOP]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Invisible Funnel Workshop/transcription_Session_13.txt\"\n```</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>133424</total_tokens><tool_uses>22</tool_uses><duration_ms>293546</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a4fcc8117f50967f7.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-07T19:37:45.927487", "_id": "1818b14c"}
