{"type": "user_message", "content": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a1f0b1e1aeb67d59a</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_019AeVjJK77pGrkB4irXo3ow</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1f0b1e1aeb67d59a.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract Agent-A DNA elements\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have enough content from all 11 files to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the extraction.\n\nBased on my thorough reading of all 11 Black Box transcription files, here are the extracted DNA elements:\n\n---\n\n## L1 - PHILOSOPHIES\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-099\"\n        statement: \"Your success is up to you. Every time someone has been frustrated and blamed something else, it's them not being willing to acknowledge the fact that they didn't work hard. I'm giving you the exact same blueprint I use every single day to make tens of millions of dollars.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Personal responsibility in coaching programs\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-100\"\n        statement: \"The people who get into programs and their mind is set 'I gotta make money' rarely end up making money. Those who say 'this marketing thing is cool and exciting and I've got to learn how to do this better' and focus on the learning - those are the ones who become successful.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Learning mindset vs money-chasing mindset\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-101\"\n        statement: \"Don't tie yourself so much to the results of what you're building right now as much as learning the process. After you've learned an", "metadata": {"session_id": "d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\d57700cd-64b4-4d76-b212-8e7a22a24264.jsonl", "cwd": "C:\\Users\\ISMAEL_MELLO\\Downloads\\mega-brain-premium", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a1f0b1e1aeb67d59a</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_019AeVjJK77pGrkB4irXo3ow</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1f0b1e1aeb67d59a.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract Agent-A DNA elements\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have enough content from all 11 files to extract the DNA elements. Let me compile the extraction.\n\nBased on my thorough reading of all 11 Black Box transcription files, here are the extracted DNA elements:\n\n---\n\n## L1 - PHILOSOPHIES\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-099\"\n        statement: \"Your success is up to you. Every time someone has been frustrated and blamed something else, it's them not being willing to acknowledge the fact that they didn't work hard. I'm giving you the exact same blueprint I use every single day to make tens of millions of dollars.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Personal responsibility in coaching programs\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-100\"\n        statement: \"The people who get into programs and their mind is set 'I gotta make money' rarely end up making money. Those who say 'this marketing thing is cool and exciting and I've got to learn how to do this better' and focus on the learning - those are the ones who become successful.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Learning mindset vs money-chasing mindset\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-101\"\n        statement: \"Don't tie yourself so much to the results of what you're building right now as much as learning the process. After you've learned and gone through it once, you'll be able to replicate it and do it again in any business you want.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Process mastery over outcome attachment\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-102\"\n        statement: \"The biggest reason why people don't ever succeed is not because the information taught is not right or good or powerful - the biggest reason is they don't ever consume the information. Force consumption because if you can force people to consume, it'll change their lives.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Forced consumption principle\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-103\"\n        statement: \"If you want rabid consumers, you've got to be a little bit more on the fringe. The fringe is where people buy things. You can't be giving generalized knowledge - you got to have your own weird system, this is the only way it works.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Prolific positioning on the fringe\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-104\"\n        statement: \"Typical internet marketers think 'if I give them a product that's useful but incomplete they'll have to buy my next thing.' No - you want to give them everything. Your goal is that 95% of them will leave and self-implement. The 5-10% who want more will come to you for your magic bullet.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Give everything vs incomplete product philosophy\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-105\"\n        statement: \"Goals don't mean anything anymore. If you want to inspire people and yourself, you can't have goals - you've got to have a vision. With your free thing, you got to set a vision for people. Vision is what people buy into.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Vision over goals for customer inspiration\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-106\"\n        statement: \"The Black Box application funnel is not about tricking someone or using sneaky sales tactics. It's about putting up barriers and filters to keep out everyone except the people who are ready and willing right now. You want the cream of the crop to rise to the top.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Barrier-based selling philosophy\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"PHI-RB-107\"\n        statement: \"The key to this video script is just your excitement. The excitement and the energy and my emotion is what sold it. A two-minute iPhone video of me just holding up the product out-converted the best professional sales copy we had.\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Authenticity and excitement over polished copy\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n```\n\n## L2 - MENTAL MODELS\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MM-RB-083\"\n        name: \"The Black Box Model\"\n        description: \"A three-step funnel system where you plug any business in one end, and cash falls out the other. Step 1: Buyer Magnet (free+shipping). Step 2: Invisible Funnel (premium webinar, $0 down, credit card on file, bill later). Step 3: Black Box (high-ticket application funnel). Each step works standalone but combined in sequence creates exponential results.\"\n        application: \"Building a complete customer ascension funnel from cold traffic to high-ticket backend\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-084\"\n        name: \"The 100 Visitor Test\"\n        description: \"Send 100 visitors to a $197 product page: 1% conversion = $197 revenue, 1 customer. Send same 100 visitors to free+shipping offer: 8% conversion = 8 buyers, then 25% take the $197 upsell = $394 revenue, 8 customers. Free+shipping front end nearly doubles revenue and creates 7x more buyers from identical traffic.\"\n        application: \"Proving the mathematical superiority of free+shipping funnels over direct sales pages\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-085\"\n        name: \"Three Prerequisites Model\"\n        description: \"To make the Black Box system work, you need three things: (1) A Secret - your unique prolific hook that grabs attention, (2) A Case Study - proof that someone else (not you) achieved results with your system, (3) A System - your step-by-step process broken into chapters/modules/steps that takes someone to a desired result.\"\n        application: \"Validating readiness to build a funnel - if missing any of the three, fix that first\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-086\"\n        name: \"Commitment Escalation Through Engagement\"\n        description: \"During invisible funnel webinars, after each concept taught, post in a Facebook group asking for the audience's number one takeaway. Wait until a critical mass (150-200 comments) before continuing. This creates the law of commitment - when people have said yes publicly multiple times, they are far more likely to say yes to the final offer.\"\n        application: \"Maximizing invisible funnel close rates through progressive public micro-commitments\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-087\"\n        name: \"Scheduled Consumption Model\"\n        description: \"People are more likely to consume and act upon content if they have to schedule when they receive it. If you just put content on a download page, most people never watch it. By making them show up at a scheduled time (like the invisible funnel), you get 75%+ live attendance vs near-zero consumption on a download page. The future of content delivery is scheduled, not on-demand.\"\n        application: \"Designing delivery systems that force consumption rather than passive access\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MM-RB-088\"\n        name: \"Same Content, Different Packaging\"\n        description: \"The content you teach in a free DVD, a $97 invisible funnel, and a $5,000+ coaching program is identical - the same system, the same steps. The difference is the format and proximity to you. Free DVD = self-study. Invisible funnel = group training. Coaching = personal hand-holding. People pay more for closer access to you, not for different information.\"\n        application: \"Structuring a value ladder where the same core system is packaged at multiple price points\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n```\n\n## L3 - HEURISTICS\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-132\"\n        rule: \"On free+shipping offers, expect an 8-10% conversion rate on the landing page, and approximately 25% of those buyers will take the upsell.\"\n        threshold: \"8-10% opt-in rate on free+shipping page; 25% upsell take rate\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Free plus shipping funnel metrics\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-133\"\n        rule: \"On invisible funnel webinars, expect around 85% live show-up rate (vs 20% on typical free webinars) because people have put their credit card in and need to decide if the content is worth paying for.\"\n        threshold: \"85% show-up rate with credit card on file; 20% show-up rate without\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Invisible funnel attendance metrics\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-134\"\n        rule: \"On invisible funnels, the refund/cancellation rate with your own merchant account stays under 10%. Using PayPal, expect 20-30% cancellation rate because people can cancel without talking to anyone.\"\n        threshold: \"<10% cancellation with merchant account; 20-30% with PayPal\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Payment processor impact on refund rates\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-135\"\n        rule: \"Offer a pre-pay discount on invisible funnels (e.g. save $20 by paying upfront). Expect around 39% of registrants to pre-pay, and this percentage increases the more trust you've built with your audience.\"\n        threshold: \"~39% pre-pay rate on first invisible funnel with existing audience\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Pre-payment option on invisible funnels\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-136\"\n        rule: \"For the buyer magnet video, the script should take only 60 seconds to 2 minutes max. Answer four questions: Who are you? What do you have? Why do they need it? How can they get it? Record on an iPhone. A simple excited video outperforms professional sales copy.\"\n        threshold: \"60-120 seconds max for buyer magnet video; 4 questions\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Buyer magnet video script length and format\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-137\"\n        rule: \"Only about 2-3% of buyers will click on the application page banner directly after purchase. Use a 30-day email drip sequence to push the remaining buyers toward the application over time. Expect 5-10% total application rate over that period.\"\n        threshold: \"2-3% immediate application rate; 5-10% over 30-day drip\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - High-ticket application conversion timing\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-138\"\n        rule: \"Block out at least two hours a day for the first two to three months when building out your funnel. One day per week should be dedicated entirely to learning, the rest of the week to implementation. Complete each step before moving to the next.\"\n        threshold: \"2 hours/day minimum; 1 study day + implementation week cycle\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Implementation schedule for coaching students\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_1_Blackbox_Introduction.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-139\"\n        rule: \"When the word 'free' is introduced, 90% of people shift to the free option even when a superior alternative costs only pennies more. This is the 'power of free' from Predictably Irrational - dropping from 1 cent to free has a disproportionate psychological impact.\"\n        threshold: \"90% choose free vs 50/50 split at any price above zero\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Psychology of free pricing\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"HEUR-RB-140\"\n        rule: \"For high-ticket application forms, make them long and detailed on purpose. Ask about their business, current results, marketing budget, and Dan Sullivan's 3-year question. Long applications act as filters - if they won't fill out a big application, they're probably not a buyer who will spend money.\"\n        threshold: \"Application acts as qualification filter; include financial qualification questions\"\n        context: \"Invisible Funnel - Black Box - Application form as buyer qualification tool\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n```\n\n## L4 - FRAMEWORKS\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"FW-RB-085\"\n        name: \"Black Box Funnel Architecture\"\n        components: \"Step 1: Buyer Magnet (free+shipping CD/DVD/book with two-step order form - shipping address first, credit card second). Step 2: Case Study Upsell (video showing someone else's results with the product just purchased). Step 3: Invisible Funnel Registration ($0 down, credit card on file, premium webinar). Step 4: Invisible Funnel Delivery (teach entire system, give everything). Step 5: Application Page (video + long form application for high-ticket coaching).\"\n        application: \"Complete end-to-end funnel from cold traffic to high-ticket backend sales\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-086\"\n        name: \"Who-What-Why-How Video Script\"\n        components: \"(1) Who are you? - State your name and brief credibility. (2) What do you have? - Show the physical product, describe what it does. (3) Why do they need it? - Connect to their pain point, paint the benefit picture. (4) How can they get it? - Direct call to action to the order form. Learned from copywriter John Carlton - these are the only four questions any sales piece needs to answer.\"\n        application: \"Creating buyer magnet videos, case study videos, and any short sales video in 60-120 seconds\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_3B.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-087\"\n        name: \"Two-Step Buyer Squeeze Page\"\n        components: \"Step 1: Headline + bullet points + product image + form asking 'Where should I ship this to?' (shipping address only). Step 2: Credit card collection page. This two-step process captures contact info of 30-40% of visitors before payment, allowing follow-up with non-buyers. Outperforms traditional one-step order forms.\"\n        application: \"Maximizing buyer magnet conversions and building a follow-up list from non-completers\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-088\"\n        name: \"Invisible Funnel Mechanics\"\n        components: \"(1) Prospect registers with credit card for $0. (2) Optional: offer pre-pay discount (save $10-20). (3) Scheduled webinar (not on-demand) delivering premium training (1-4 hours). (4) Teach entire system - hold nothing back. (5) 3-day evaluation window: if satisfied, card is billed the agreed price; if not, email before billing date to cancel. (6) Offer magic bullet/application at end.\"\n        application: \"Selling premium training content with zero risk to the buyer while achieving 85%+ show-up rates\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-089\"\n        name: \"High-Ticket Application Funnel\"\n        components: \"(1) Banner on every thank-you page: 'Need my help? I'm not talking about another course - I want to design the system with you.' (2) Short video explaining the offer and providing a bribe (e.g., free strategy call). (3) Detailed application form with qualifying questions: business details, current revenue, marketing budget, list size, Dan Sullivan's 3-year vision question. (4) Phone call from sales team using specific script. (5) 30-day email drip pushing non-appliers back to application.\"\n        application: \"Converting invisible funnel attendees into high-ticket coaching clients ($5K-$100K)\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-090\"\n        name: \"Reverse Value Ladder Creation\"\n        components: \"Instead of building bottom-up (book first), build top-down: (1) Start with a live seminar/workshop (highest value, easiest to create, just teach). (2) Strip out videos to create home study course. (3) Strip out audios for audio version. (4) Transcribe to create the book. This way you create the highest-priced, highest-value product first and derive all lower-tier products from it.\"\n        application: \"Rapidly creating an entire product suite from a single live event recording\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-091\"\n        name: \"Instant Result Invisible Funnel Design\"\n        components: \"The invisible funnel must deliver an instant, tangible result during the training itself. Examples: (1) Howard Berg's speed reading - double your reading speed in 4 hours (test before and after). (2) Dating guru - use these techniques to get a date this weekend. (3) Couponing - save $100 on your next grocery bill. (4) Business - build your first funnel page by end of webinar. The instant result is what makes people happy to pay.\"\n        application: \"Designing invisible funnel content that delivers measurable outcomes within the training window\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-092\"\n        name: \"Buyer Magnet Adaptation by Business Type\"\n        components: \"Author/Coach/Consultant: Pull out your best secret from your system, make a CD/DVD. E-commerce: Create informational CD related to your product category (e.g., 'how to train your parrot' for bird cage store). Network Marketing: Create TWO buyer magnets - one for product consumers, one for opportunity seekers. Affiliate Marketing: Create a free CD teaching your best secret in the niche, build a list, then promote affiliate products. Local/Offline: Create educational DVD about your specialty area.\"\n        application: \"Adapting the free+shipping buyer magnet concept to any business model\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"FW-RB-093\"\n        name: \"Survey-Based Market Research (Ask Campaign)\"\n        components: \"(1) Survey your existing list/customers asking 'What is your #1 question about [topic]?' (2) If insufficient responses: join Facebook groups in your niche and post conversation-starting questions. (3) Search forums (sort by most views) to find what questions people are already asking. (4) Use the most popular questions to build your system outline/table of contents. (5) Reading forum responses on popular threads makes you an expert in hours.\"\n        application: \"Rapidly validating product ideas and building system outlines from real market demand\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Not_Getting_Answers_to_Your_Survey.txt\"\n```\n\n## L5 - METHODOLOGIES\n\n```yaml\n      - id: \"MET-RB-048\"\n        name: \"Black Box Funnel Build-Out Methodology\"\n        steps: \"Week 1: Create your system outline using Ask Campaign survey data. Week 2: Create your buyer magnet (free CD/DVD) - record Who-What-Why-How video, submit to DiscDelivered for print-on-demand ($50 setup, $5.99/unit). Week 3: Build invisible funnel registration page and record your premium webinar teaching your complete system. Week 4: Record your case study/magic bullet sales video. Week 5: Build application page with qualifying form. Weeks 6-8: Set up traffic systems, email sequences, and phone sales process.\"\n        application: \"8-week step-by-step implementation of a complete Black Box funnel from scratch\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Blackbox_Quickstart.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-049\"\n        name: \"System Creation from Scratch Methodology\"\n        steps: \"(1) Identify your passion/expertise area. (2) Write down the step-by-step process you would teach someone - each step becomes a chapter/module. (3) If you don't have expertise, become a 'sponge' - read every book, interview every expert, join forums, consume everything. (4) Organize the collected knowledge into YOUR system with YOUR sequencing. (5) Test-teach it live to a small group (even friends). (6) Record the live teaching. (7) The recording becomes your first product; the outline becomes your system.\"\n        application: \"Creating a marketable system even when starting from zero expertise\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-050\"\n        name: \"Print-on-Demand Buyer Magnet Testing\"\n        steps: \"(1) Identify your best secret/hook for a free+shipping offer. (2) Record a CD/DVD covering that one topic. (3) Submit to DiscDelivered.com - $50 setup fee, $5.99/unit print-on-demand (no inventory). (4) Create a two-step landing page (shipping address â†’ credit card). (5) Record 60-second iPhone video using Who-What-Why-How script. (6) Drive small test traffic. (7) If it converts, scale. If not, test a different hook with zero sunk cost since it's print-on-demand.\"\n        application: \"Risk-free testing of multiple buyer magnet ideas without inventory investment\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-051\"\n        name: \"First High-Ticket Coaching Launch Methodology\"\n        steps: \"(1) Email your existing buyers/list asking if they'd be interested in direct coaching. (2) Gauge interest from responses. (3) Put up a simple page with a PayPal button - describe the coaching program format (weekly calls for 6-8 weeks). (4) Start with a price that scares you slightly ($500-$5,000). (5) Sell to initial group. (6) Invite friends to fill the room if needed. (7) Record everything. (8) The recording becomes a home study course for the next tier of your value ladder.\"\n        application: \"Launching a high-ticket backend offer with minimal infrastructure\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-052\"\n        name: \"Application Funnel Qualification Process\"\n        steps: \"(1) Place 'Need my help?' banner on all thank-you pages. (2) Video on application landing page: acknowledge they came through your funnel (proof it works), offer a bribe (strategy call + bonus materials) contingent on completing application. (3) Application form collects: business details, current revenue, marketing budget, list size, biggest problem, Dan Sullivan's 3-year question. (4) Review applications before calling - know their business. (5) Sales call: reference their application answers, position coaching as solution to their stated problems.\"\n        application: \"Qualifying and converting high-ticket coaching applicants through a structured process\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Module_5.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-053\"\n        name: \"Forum-Based Expert Building Methodology\"\n        steps: \"(1) Go to Google, search '[your topic] forum'. (2) Find forums with 10,000+ active members. (3) Sort forum posts by most views/replies to find the most popular questions. (4) Read the top 20-30 most-viewed threads completely - by the time you finish, you'll be an expert. (5) Use the most popular questions as your system outline chapters. (6) Join Facebook groups in your niche (15,000+ members). (7) Post conversation-starting questions (be slightly controversial to generate engagement). (8) Network individually with active members.\"\n        application: \"Becoming a recognized expert and building a product outline in any niche within days\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_Not_Getting_Answers_to_Your_Survey.txt\"\n\n      - id: \"MET-RB-054\"\n        name: \"Dagan Smith Invisible Funnel Engagement Method\"\n        steps: \"(1) Teach concept #1 of your system on the webinar. (2) Post in Facebook group: 'Give me your #1 takeaway from concept #1.' (3) Wait until 150-200 comments come in - do NOT continue until engagement threshold is met. (4) Teach concept #2, repeat the posting and waiting process. (5) Continue for each concept in your system. (6) At the end, post: 'Who here wants to work with me on this?' - get 100-200+ public 'yes' responses. (7) Follow up on Facebook with anyone who said yes but didn't apply - screenshot their commitment and send it to them. This method drove $210,000 in sales for Greg Davis in one invisible funnel.\"\n        application: \"Maximizing invisible funnel conversion through progressive public micro-commitments\"\n        module_sources: [IF-BLACKBOX]\n        raw_source: \"knowledge/sources/russell-brunson/raw/08._Funnel_Immersion/Invisible Funnel/Black Box/transcription_2_Blackbox_Overview.txt\"\n```</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>150183</total_tokens><tool_uses>36</tool_uses><duration_ms>354940</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: C:\\Users\\ISMAEL~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\claude\\C--Users-ISMAEL-MELLO-Downloads-mega-brain-premium\\tasks\\a1f0b1e1aeb67d59a.output"}, "_timestamp": "2026-03-07T19:43:49.134398", "_id": "85b2b66d"}
